5:001049694	6:gr-1049694	3:Poems	4:book review	60:Poems	61:John Keats	62:1997	64:Everyman Paperbacks	68:read	63:9780460878081	67:4/5	71:https://www.goodreads.com/book/show/1049694
5:000000105	6:gr-105	3:Chapterhouse: Dune (Dune #6)	4:book review	60:Chapterhouse: Dune (Dune #6)	61:Frank Herbert	62:1987	64:Ace Books	68:read	69:2018-09-29	67:5/5	70:This is the most difficult of the Dune books to review. On the one hand, it's extremely slow owing to the extraordinary amount of Bene Gesserit internal monologues. On the other hand, it finally reveals the inner-workings of some of the biggest mysteries in the series. Finally, it leaves us with an incredible set of cliffhangers. \n\nFor what it is, the book is superb. Were there a proper follow up by Frank himself, I'd say this would be one of people's favorites. As a finale to the series, it sucks.	71:https://www.goodreads.com/book/show/105
