5:010664113	6:gr-10664113	3:A Dance with Dragons (A Song of Ice and Fire, #5)	4:book review	60:A Dance with Dragons (A Song of Ice and Fire, #5)	61:George R.R. Martin	62:2011	64:Bantam	68:read	69:2011-09-22	67:4/5	70:Quite solid. It was good to see so many of my favorite characters again. I hope it's not another half a decade before the next book.	71:https://www.goodreads.com/book/show/10664113
5:010754266	6:gr-10754266	3:The Written (Emaneska #1)	4:book review	60:The Written (Emaneska #1)	61:Ben Galley	62:2011	64:BenGalley.com	68:read	69:2012-04-18	63:9780956770011	67:1/5	70:I don't feel like spending a long time tearing this book apart, so I'll just say it briefly. The writing is just very poor.\n\n"All of a sudden" and its like are overused. The drama is summarized and told rather than shown.  The characters are flat and seem to be the author's favorite D&D personas, not real people. Descriptions are filled with mad-lib-esque adjectives of a poor, and often repetitive, nature. Nothing pops.\n\nI'll be honest. I picked it up because of the cover art, and it just wasn't worth it.	71:https://www.goodreads.com/book/show/10754266
