5:000010799	6:gr-10799	3:A Farewell to Arms	4:book review	60:A Farewell to Arms	61:Ernest Hemingway	62:2004	64:Arrow Books	68:read	69:1999-01-01	63:9780099910107	67:2/5	71:https://www.goodreads.com/book/show/10799
5:010803121	6:gr-10803121	3:The Alloy of Law (Mistborn, #4)	4:book review	60:The Alloy of Law (Mistborn, #4)	61:Brandon Sanderson	62:2011	64:Tor Books	68:read	69:2014-07-05	63:9780765330420	67:3/5	71:https://www.goodreads.com/book/show/10803121
5:010853915	6:gr-10853915	3:Tvær galdraskræður	4:book review	60:Tvær galdraskræður	61:Magnús Rafnsson	62:2008	64:Strandagaldur	68:read	69:2022-07-03	63:9789979958451	67:5/5	70:An utterly fascinating collection of Icelandic magical grimoires from the 17th/18th centuries translated into modern Icelandic and English (and a bit of Latin) with diagrams and notes. Historian Magnús Rafnsson has done an excellent job pulling this together and giving it some structure. What's left paints a fascinating picture of the great steps and detail work that went into the sorcery of the times, and what special needs drove such actions in the face of persecutions and burning. If you're interested in the history of this type of sorcery I would also recommend stopping in at the Museum of Icelandic Sorcery and Witchcraft in the Westfjörds. They have extensive displays and documents from this time period.	71:https://www.goodreads.com/book/show/10853915
