5:000011991	6:gr-11991	3:The Fall	4:book review	60:The Fall	61:Albert Camus	62:1991	64:Vintage Books	68:read	69:2022-06-08	63:9780679720225	67:3/5	70:The Fall is delivered as a series of soliloquies confessing more and more of the nature of our unreliable narrator, filled with eloquence of language professed as his weakness and pleasure, serving to take us forth on a journey of character devolving under the realization of his own ethical failings. The city serves as a colorful backdrop and supporting symbolism for this fall from the great heights so beloved of the narrator--and mirrored in his professional and personal life--to its position below sea level and at the center of the concentric canals which he equates to Dante's tiers of hell. \n\nIt's a wonderful little novela.	71:https://www.goodreads.com/book/show/11991
