5:018815219	6:gr-18815219	3:Holy Bible: New American Standard Bible (NASB)	4:book review	60:Holy Bible: New American Standard Bible (NASB)	61:Anonymous	62:2013	64:The Lockman Foundation	68:read	69:2014-01-01	67:5/5	71:https://www.goodreads.com/book/show/18815219
5:000001885	6:gr-1885	3:Pride and Prejudice	4:book review	60:Pride and Prejudice	61:Jane Austen	62:2000	64:Modern Library	68:read	67:5/5	71:https://www.goodreads.com/book/show/1885
5:000188572	6:gr-188572	3:The Complete Sherlock Holmes	4:book review	60:The Complete Sherlock Holmes	61:Arthur Conan Doyle	62:1986	64:Bantam Classics	68:read	69:2011-01-01	67:4/5	71:https://www.goodreads.com/book/show/188572
5:018869177	6:gr-18869177	3:Lying	4:book review	60:Lying	61:Sam Harris	62:2013	64:Four Elephants Press	68:read	69:2015-12-26	67:2/5	70:Some interesting thoughts and arguments, but he shies away from the deepest ethical arguments and relies too heavily on a few assumptions not fully expressed: lying will always eventually be "caught", in any situation where lying seems justified there is a non-lying alternative that is better by nature of not having to lie, the energy required in lying makes it less desirable than truth-telling. While I feel many of his conclusions were accurate or at least thought-provoking, I was left generally unsatisfied with the arguments leading there. The most interesting portion of the book was a section on responses to reader's questions given at the end.	71:https://www.goodreads.com/book/show/18869177
5:018873816	6:gr-18873816	3:The Huntsman's Amulet (Society of the Sword, #2)	4:book review	60:The Huntsman's Amulet (Society of the Sword, #2)	61:Duncan M. Hamilton	62:2013	68:read	69:2019-01-18	67:2/5	70:See my review of [b:The Tattered Banner|17557803|The Tattered Banner (Society of the Sword, #1)|Duncan M. Hamilton|https://images.gr-assets.com/books/1362480716s/17557803.jpg|24484894]	71:https://www.goodreads.com/book/show/18873816
5:018883016	6:gr-18883016	3:The Last Oracle (The Chronicles of Lumineia: The White Mage Saga, #1)	4:book review	60:The Last Oracle (The Chronicles of Lumineia: The White Mage Saga, #1)	61:Ben Hale	62:2013	64:Snowlight Publishing	68:read	69:2016-06-18	67:4/5	70:Yes, yes, yes, it's a complete rip off of Harry Potter. Even so, Ben has done a great job world building and designing his magic system. I rolled my eyes at first but the story sucked me in and carried me along. I genuinely liked the few main characters, and the writing was pretty strong.\n\nDialogue among the main, modern characters sounded fairly natural, but the aspects of the story that leaned deeper into fantasy read over-the-top. The tone couldn't find a clear foothold and some of the plot was rushed. \n\nAll in all, it was a very fun, quick read. I'll be finishing the series soon.	71:https://www.goodreads.com/book/show/18883016
5:018966322	6:gr-18966322	3:Mitosis (The Reckoners, #1.5)	4:book review	60:Mitosis (The Reckoners, #1.5)	61:Brandon Sanderson	62:2013	64:Delacorte Press	68:read	69:2015-03-30	63:9780449818435	67:3/5	71:https://www.goodreads.com/book/show/18966322
5:018966806	6:gr-18966806	3:Morning Star (Red Rising Saga, #3)	4:book review	60:Morning Star (Red Rising Saga, #3)	61:Pierce Brown	62:2016	64:Del Rey	68:read	69:2015-10-21	63:9780345539847	67:5/5	70:A solid ending to the series	71:https://www.goodreads.com/book/show/18966806
5:018966819	6:gr-18966819	3:Golden Son (Red Rising Saga, #2)	4:book review	60:Golden Son (Red Rising Saga, #2)	61:Pierce Brown	62:2015	64:Del Rey	68:read	69:2015-09-14	63:9780345539823	67:5/5	71:https://www.goodreads.com/book/show/18966819
5:000189783	6:gr-189783	3:The Elfstones of Shannara  (The Original Shannara Trilogy, #2)	4:book review	60:The Elfstones of Shannara  (The Original Shannara Trilogy, #2)	61:Terry Brooks	62:2003	64:Books on Tape	68:read	69:2018-11-05	63:9780736693417	67:2/5	71:https://www.goodreads.com/book/show/189783
5:019056206	6:gr-19056206	3:Of Myth and Magick	4:book review	60:Of Myth and Magick	61:M.E. Brines	62:2011	64:Smashwords Edition	68:read	69:2021-09-14	63:1465942947	67:1/5	70:I'm not sure where this came from. It was on my Kindle so I probably found it online for free. First off, it's not a book. At best it's a short essay. Second, it's almost entirely wrong about every single point made. It reads like a high schoolers angry generalization of religion and science without any depth of understanding of either. It draws nonsensical conclusions from nowhere and runs down lines of conjecture that begin on false premises and get flimsier from there. Don't waste your time.	71:https://www.goodreads.com/book/show/19056206
5:000019068	6:gr-19068	3:The Nicomachean Ethics	4:book review	60:The Nicomachean Ethics	61:Aristotle	62:2004	64:Penguin Classics	68:read	69:2022-01-12	63:9780140449495	67:3/5	70:Dear lord. Aristotle is thorough! Logical induction meets ethics in this classic work and doesn't stop until the last page. There are full stretches and really interesting ones throughout. Despite the age of the work it's easily understood.\n\nI felt like every page contains about three "yeah, but..." moments that need exploring. Thankfully I have the next few thousand years of ethics writings to get through which do just that.	71:https://www.goodreads.com/book/show/19068
5:000190917	6:gr-190917	3:The Cave of Time (Choose Your Own Adventure, #1)	4:book review	60:The Cave of Time (Choose Your Own Adventure, #1)	61:Edward Packard	62:1982	64:Bantam Books	68:read	69:2018-10-04	63:9780553269659	67:3/5	70:There were a lot of disappointing endings in this story. It's not that the endings were bad, but they left too much hanging and didn't feel as decisive as most CYOA books do. Of course, this was the first, so it gets extra points for starting the awesomeness.	71:https://www.goodreads.com/book/show/190917
5:000190930	6:gr-190930	3:The Abominable Snowman (Choose Your Own Adventure, #13)	4:book review	60:The Abominable Snowman (Choose Your Own Adventure, #13)	61:R.A. Montgomery	62:2006	64:Chooseco	68:read	69:2018-10-19	63:9781933390017	67:3/5	71:https://www.goodreads.com/book/show/190930
5:000190957	6:gr-190957	3:Prisoner of the Ant People (Choose Your Own Adventure, #25)	4:book review	60:Prisoner of the Ant People (Choose Your Own Adventure, #25)	61:R.A. Montgomery	62:2006	64:Chooseco	68:read	69:2019-02-14	63:9781933390109	67:4/5	70:I had a ton of fun reading this one tonight. The book got a lot of hype from an article on SyFyWire (https://www.syfy.com/syfywire/choose-your-own-demise-prisoner-of-the-ant-people) and it didn't really live up to it. Still, despite not having nearly as much horrible death as suggested, it was well written with interesting and varied storylines. Everything wasn't railroaded and the book didn't waste time with fake choices like, "will you go on an adventure or will you go to sleep?".	71:https://www.goodreads.com/book/show/190957
5:000190988	6:gr-190988	3:Trouble on Planet Earth (Choose Your Own Adventure, #29)	4:book review	60:Trouble on Planet Earth (Choose Your Own Adventure, #29)	61:R.A. Montgomery	62:2006	64:Chooseco	68:read	69:2019-04-28	63:9781933390116	67:4/5	70:This book has the charm of weirdness. The endings are quite varied and I never felt railroaded into a single path. Deaths aplenty in these pages!	71:https://www.goodreads.com/book/show/190988
