5:020426102	6:gr-20426102	3:Nice Dragons Finish Last (Heartstrikers, #1)	4:book review	60:Nice Dragons Finish Last (Heartstrikers, #1)	61:Rachel Aaron	62:2014	64:Aaron/Bach, LLC	68:read	69:2018-05-06	67:2/5	71:https://www.goodreads.com/book/show/20426102
5:000204779	6:gr-204779	3:The Masque of the Red Death	4:book review	60:The Masque of the Red Death	61:Edgar Allan Poe	62:2004	64:BookSurge Classics	68:read	63:9781594567391	67:4/5	71:https://www.goodreads.com/book/show/204779
5:020501606	6:gr-20501606	3:Futuristic Violence and Fancy Suits (Zoey Ashe, #1)	4:book review	60:Futuristic Violence and Fancy Suits (Zoey Ashe, #1)	61:David  Wong	62:2015	64:Thomas Dunne Books	68:read	69:2016-11-13	63:9781250040190	67:3/5	70:This book was a lot of fun, but the storyline was nonsensical. Most of the action didn't need to take place and it wasn't so much driven by the main character as by the random whims of the author. The narration in the audiobook is tricky to review. On the one hand, the narrator had a hard time keeping the cadence of the text, and would pause awkwardly in the middle of phrases in a disconnected way. Also, how on Earth did they manage to make the entire audiobook without a single person telling the narrator how to pronounce tabula rasa? All that aside, she was a good fit for the voice of the main character. So there's that, I guess.\n\nIn short, it was a fun read, but I won't go out of my way to recommend it.	71:https://www.goodreads.com/book/show/20501606
