5:020766595	6:gr-20766595	3:Red Rising (Red Rising, #1)	4:book review	60:Red Rising (Red Rising, #1)	61:Pierce Brown	62:2014	64:Del Rey	68:read	69:2015-01-01	67:4/5	70:Not sure why this was still on my to-read shelf.	71:https://www.goodreads.com/book/show/20766595
5:000208123	6:gr-208123	3:The Tibetan Book of the Dead	4:book review	60:The Tibetan Book of the Dead	61:Padmasambhava	62:2007	64:Penguin Classics	68:read	69:2013-08-03	63:9780143104940	67:4/5	70:This read was primarily done for research purposes but the content was interesting enough to make it a pleasure. My favorite part was actually the preface to the version I read which was written by Carl Jung and gave a depth to things I would have missed otherwise. The content of the book itself was difficult to comprehend on its own, but there are a number of outside resources that helped with that, including trusty old Wikipedia. If you are a student of comparative religion, interested in the Bardo, or looking for some fresh ideas for the Sacred nature in your own writing, then please read this book.	71:https://www.goodreads.com/book/show/208123
