5:000216363	6:gr-216363	3:The Man in the High Castle	4:book review	60:The Man in the High Castle	61:Philip K. Dick	62:1992	64:Vintage	68:read	69:2016-07-09	63:9780679740674	67:3/5	70:The book read well as it progressed, but I was disappointed by the climax and resolution. It felt less impactful than it should have been. The stories didn't tie together as closely as I'd wanted, and the overall message didn't land for me.\n\nI'm surprised to be enjoying the Amazon TV series more than the book.	71:https://www.goodreads.com/book/show/216363
5:000216422	6:gr-216422	3:The Last Command (Star Wars: The Thrawn Trilogy, #3)	4:book review	60:The Last Command (Star Wars: The Thrawn Trilogy, #3)	61:Timothy Zahn	62:1993	64:Random House Worlds	68:read	69:2020-01-15	63:9780553564921	67:5/5	70:The way it should have ended	71:https://www.goodreads.com/book/show/216422
5:000216442	6:gr-216442	3:Dark Force Rising (Star Wars: The Thrawn Trilogy, #2)	4:book review	60:Dark Force Rising (Star Wars: The Thrawn Trilogy, #2)	61:Timothy Zahn	62:1993	64:Random House Worlds	68:read	69:2020-01-07	63:9780553560718	67:4/5	70:Not as strong as part 1. It gets itself a little bit tied up in coincidence beyond those that can be explained away by Jedi following the force. The ending could have been a bit darker too, which would have added pressure for the start of book 3. All this is nitpicking though. This is THE Star Wars continuation.	71:https://www.goodreads.com/book/show/216442
5:000217782	6:gr-217782	3:Line of Fire (Star Trek: The Next Generation - Starfleet Academy, #2)	4:book review	60:Line of Fire (Star Trek: The Next Generation - Starfleet Academy, #2)	61:Peter David	62:1993	64:Pocket Books	68:read	69:2016-03-25	63:9780671870850	67:3/5	71:https://www.goodreads.com/book/show/217782
5:000217786	6:gr-217786	3:Starfall (Star Trek: The Next Generation - Starfleet Academy, #8)	4:book review	60:Starfall (Star Trek: The Next Generation - Starfleet Academy, #8)	61:Brad Strickland	62:1995	64:Aladdin Paperbacks	68:read	69:2016-07-03	63:9780671510107	67:4/5	70:These books have been expectedly simplistic to date. Starfall was a pleasant surprise, bringing a deeper introspection instead of relying upon storybook action. Mr. Strickland proved himself to be an excellent writer, even with early-age fiction. It was a pleasure to read.	71:https://www.goodreads.com/book/show/217786
5:000217829	6:gr-217829	3:Ghost Ship (Star Trek: The Next Generation #1)	4:book review	60:Ghost Ship (Star Trek: The Next Generation #1)	61:Diane Carey	62:1991	64:Pocket Books	68:read	69:2010-12-04	63:9780671746087	67:2/5	70:I saw this sitting on my Kindle and decided to give it a shot. I guess I can blame most of the character differentiation on the age of the book, and the fact that they were dealing with season one characters. Still, it gave me the feeling that the author just didn't "get it" in parts. Oh, and warp 13? Hrm....	71:https://www.goodreads.com/book/show/217829
