5:024683898	6:gr-24683898	3:The Death of Dulgath (The Riyria Chronicles, #3)	4:book review	60:The Death of Dulgath (The Riyria Chronicles, #3)	61:Michael J. Sullivan	62:2015	64:Riyria Enterprises, LLC	68:read	69:2017-07-09	63:9781943363001	67:3/5	71:https://www.goodreads.com/book/show/24683898
5:002473980	6:gr-2473980	3:Start Spinning: Everything You Need to Know to Make Great Yarn	4:book review	60:Start Spinning: Everything You Need to Know to Make Great Yarn	61:Maggie Casey	62:2008	64:Interweave	68:read	69:2017-10-14	63:9781596680654	67:5/5	70:Great introduction to spinning. I'll be referring back to this a great deal as I get started. This is definitely for the novice. Don't bother if you are already comfortable with your wheel.	71:https://www.goodreads.com/book/show/2473980
5:000024780	6:gr-24780	3:The Book of Three (The Chronicles of Prydain, #1)	4:book review	60:The Book of Three (The Chronicles of Prydain, #1)	61:Lloyd Alexander	62:2006	64:Square Fish	68:read	69:2021-07-19	63:9780805080483	67:2/5	70:I wanted to read this since it was the inspiration for much of the original dungeons and dragons. I see now that it's mostly in the world building, and that being pulled from Welsh mythology leaves little credit to the book itself. \n\nThere are some funny moments but ultimately the dialog felt forced and overly formal, the plot moved more due to accident and coincidence than the efforts of the characters, and the characters themselves felt flat. It's a product of it's time, I suppose.	71:https://www.goodreads.com/book/show/24780
