5:000024866	6:gr-24866	3:Dragon's Kin (Pern, #16)	4:book review	60:Dragon's Kin (Pern, #16)	61:Anne McCaffrey	62:2004	64:Del Rey	68:read	69:1998-01-01	63:9780345462008	67:3/5	71:https://www.goodreads.com/book/show/24866
5:024886854	6:gr-24886854	3:Slow Stitch: Mindful And Contemplative Textile Art	4:book review	60:Slow Stitch: Mindful And Contemplative Textile Art	61:Claire Wellesley-Smith	62:2015	64:Batsford	68:read	69:2019-07-22	63:9781849942997	67:3/5	71:https://www.goodreads.com/book/show/24886854
5:024893479	6:gr-24893479	3:Candles of Rejuvenescence	4:book review	60:Candles of Rejuvenescence	61:Shizette Parker	62:2015	64:Omega House	68:read	69:2015-05-16	63:9781505845310	66:firstreads	67:1/5	70:I had to try to get through this one four times. It was a Goodreads Giveaway, which I take very seriously. By winning that lottery I feel obligated to read the book fully and give my honest feedback. This book put that to the test.\n\nCandles of Rejuvenescence is an interesting concept poorly executed. It feels rushed, relying on too much summary, telling, and exposition and not enough of anything else. The characters are just basic templates. I don't feel it is much more helpful to go into all the specific aspects that were lacking. \n\nStill, the book was not offensively bad. It had interesting concepts and themes, but all the little problems just added up to too much.	71:https://www.goodreads.com/book/show/24893479
5:024929067	6:gr-24929067	3:Forging Divinity (The War of Broken Mirrors, #1)	4:book review	60:Forging Divinity (The War of Broken Mirrors, #1)	61:Andrew Rowe	62:2015	64:CreateSpace Independent Publishing Platform	68:read	69:2017-08-07	63:9781505886559	67:3/5	71:https://www.goodreads.com/book/show/24929067
5:000002493	6:gr-2493	3:The Time Machine	4:book review	60:The Time Machine	61:H.G. Wells	62:2002	64:Signet Classics	68:read	69:2022-12-14	67:3/5	70:Still a fun story. I listened to the Simon Vance recording this time and it was lovely.	71:https://www.goodreads.com/book/show/2493
5:024945323	6:gr-24945323	3:The Red Web: The Struggle Between Russia's Digital Dictators and the New Online Revolutionaries	4:book review	60:The Red Web: The Struggle Between Russia's Digital Dictators and the New Online Revolutionaries	61:Andrei Soldatov	62:2015	64:PublicAffairs	68:read	69:2022-03-28	63:9781610395731	67:5/5	70:Holy Moly! This book does a phenomenal job laying out the current situations the world is facing regarding Russia, whether that is the invasion of Ukraine, disinformation campaigns across social media, information filtering to the people of Russia, or the playbook we saw used in the Trump campaign and presidency. These two journalists take us on a journey back to the soviet area and back again up through the 2014 Russian involvement in Donbas with an emphasis on communications, eavesdropping, filtering, control, kompromat, and in some cases murder. Seeing the history laid out, the way the FSB has operated and continues to do so, and spending time reviewing Putin's history, goals, and actions over the years, it's really not hard to extrapolate what came next or why we are seeing what we're seeing. Even as I write this I'm learning that Novaya Gazeta has suspended service, shutting down the last independent voice in journalism in the country and ending a decades long effort to continue speaking the truth in a climate that values secrecy. Dark days are ahead for Russia.	71:https://www.goodreads.com/book/show/24945323
5:000024965	6:gr-24965	3:Fear and Trembling (Penguin Great Ideas)	4:book review	60:Fear and Trembling (Penguin Great Ideas)	61:Søren Kierkegaard	62:2006	64:Penguin Books	68:read	69:2023-06-21	63:9780143037576	67:4/5	70:I had some difficulty really deeply understanding the Abraham and Isaac argument, but I found much more empathy for the story from Tobit. The innocence of the bride and her strength of faith as a sacrifice without any apparent reason felt more approachable. In the Ignatian way I could set myself in those scenes and put on the skin of each character. From there backtracking to Abraham gives me hints at where he's going.\n\nRegardless, very well done and quite accessible text.	71:https://www.goodreads.com/book/show/24965
5:024969093	6:gr-24969093	3:Recurve (The Elemental #1)	4:book review	60:Recurve (The Elemental #1)	61:Shannon Mayer	62:2015	64:Hijinks Ink Publishing, Ltd.	68:read	69:2019-01-01	67:1/5	71:https://www.goodreads.com/book/show/24969093
