5:025066780	6:gr-25066780	3:Ms. Marvel, Vol. 4: Last Days	4:book review	60:Ms. Marvel, Vol. 4: Last Days	61:G. Willow Wilson	62:2015	64:Marvel Universe	68:read	69:2021-10-17	63:9780785197362	67:3/5	71:https://www.goodreads.com/book/show/25066780
5:025068241	6:gr-25068241	3:Tarsnap Mastery: Online Backups for the Truly Paranoid (IT Mastery)	4:book review	60:Tarsnap Mastery: Online Backups for the Truly Paranoid (IT Mastery)	61:Michael W. Lucas	62:2015	64:Tilted Windmill Press	68:read	69:2019-04-04	67:4/5	71:https://www.goodreads.com/book/show/25068241
5:025086730	6:gr-25086730	3:Forever Falls: a Montague Portal novel	4:book review	60:Forever Falls: a Montague Portal novel	61:Michael Warren Lucas	62:2015	64:Tilted Windmill Press	68:read	69:2021-04-08	67:5/5	70:I don't have a fear of heights, I really don't. I kept repeating that to myself over and over as I read Forever Falls. It's a quick, tight story with one hell of an ending but the true secret sauce is the terrifying vertigo we met along the way.	71:https://www.goodreads.com/book/show/25086730
5:025143052	6:gr-25143052	3:A Crucible of Souls (Sorcery Ascendant Sequence, #1)	4:book review	60:A Crucible of Souls (Sorcery Ascendant Sequence, #1)	61:Mitchell Hogan	62:2015	64:Harper Voyager	68:read	69:2019-06-05	67:1/5	70:Did not finish.\n\nThe story had some interesting elements. To much telling, not showing. Juvenile dialogue. Very repetitive.	71:https://www.goodreads.com/book/show/25143052
5:025181955	6:gr-25181955	3:Spellslinger (Spellslinger, #1)	4:book review	60:Spellslinger (Spellslinger, #1)	61:Sebastien de Castell	62:2017	64:Hot Key Books	68:read	69:2022-12-24	63:9781785761317	67:2/5	70:I really loved the greatcoats series. I think I was expecting more based on that. There's a fine amount of world-building and intrigue, but the twists weren't very twisty and the characters weren't as vibrant and lovable as the other series. The end of this book is telegraphed pretty hard and then it takes an obnoxious amount of time to play out. The villains are also over-the-top and lack the subtle energy I expect these days. I don't think I'll continue this series.	71:https://www.goodreads.com/book/show/25181955
5:025188109	6:gr-25188109	3:Perfect State	4:book review	60:Perfect State	61:Brandon Sanderson	62:2015	64:Dragonsteel Entertainment	68:read	69:2022-05-15	63:193857009X	67:3/5	70:Sanderson can't help but create these worlds and systems of power. They flood him and he blessedly has the ability to share them with us..I really enjoyed this beige l brief visit in Perfect State. It's a reality that raises questions, teases at morality. The choice to show it in a vignette kept it feeling fresh and protected it from a possible exhaustion. It's worth a few bucks and a couple hours.	71:https://www.goodreads.com/book/show/25188109
