5:000259836	6:gr-259836	3:Dragons of Autumn Twilight  (Dragonlance: Chronicles, #1)	4:book review	60:Dragons of Autumn Twilight  (Dragonlance: Chronicles, #1)	61:Margaret Weis	62:2000	64:Wizards of the Coast	68:read	69:2013-05-18	63:9780786915743	67:4/5	70:Reread: I listened to the audiobook for the re-read of this classic. It was without a doubt the worst reader I've ever listened to. Still, the book made me smile to remember the good times past.\n\nReread with son: We read this on ebook this time and so avoided the terrible readers. My son got to enjoy my rendition and fun voices. He loved it and we're moving on to book 2.	71:https://www.goodreads.com/book/show/259836
5:000259858	6:gr-259858	3:Dragons of a Fallen Sun (Dragonlance: The War of Souls, #1)	4:book review	60:Dragons of a Fallen Sun (Dragonlance: The War of Souls, #1)	61:Margaret Weis	62:2000	64:Wizards of the Coast	68:read	69:1994-01-01	63:9780786918072	67:2/5	71:https://www.goodreads.com/book/show/259858
5:025987394	6:gr-25987394	3:Witch Is When It All Began (A Witch P.I. Mystery, #1)	4:book review	60:Witch Is When It All Began (A Witch P.I. Mystery, #1)	61:Adele Abbott	62:2015	64:Implode Publishing Ltd	68:read	69:2016-07-10	67:3/5	70:This was a fun little book, though perhaps not the finest writing. Ms Abbot has a gift with dialogue, but her pacing and story structure could use some work. I enjoyed both the audio and written versions and found it easy and enjoyable to switch between them.	71:https://www.goodreads.com/book/show/25987394
5:000260025	6:gr-260025	3:Test of the Twins (Dragonlance: Legends, #3)	4:book review	60:Test of the Twins (Dragonlance: Legends, #3)	61:Margaret Weis	62:2004	64:Wizards of the Coast	68:read	69:1994-01-01	63:9780786933884	67:3/5	71:https://www.goodreads.com/book/show/260025
5:000260224	6:gr-260224	3:The Art of the Dragonlance Saga	4:book review	60:The Art of the Dragonlance Saga	61:Margaret Weis	62:1987	64:TSR Inc	68:read	69:2009-01-01	63:9780880384476	67:3/5	71:https://www.goodreads.com/book/show/260224
5:026031851	6:gr-26031851	3:Renegade (The Spiral Wars, #1)	4:book review	60:Renegade (The Spiral Wars, #1)	61:Joel Shepherd	62:2015	64:CreateSpace Publishing	68:read	69:2021-06-07	63:1310986789	67:4/5	70:What a fun romp! This story struck the balance between action/adventure and intrigue with a healthy dose of world(s) building. The pacing was excellent and gave appropriate time to sink deeply into the interpersonal relationships and politics while not rushing through action sequences. The cast of characters is wide with individuals precisely painted and unique enough to follow from the start. I will definitely be picking up book 2.	71:https://www.goodreads.com/book/show/26031851
5:026068046	6:gr-26068046	3:The Summer Dragon (The Evertide, #1)	4:book review	60:The Summer Dragon (The Evertide, #1)	61:Todd Lockwood	62:2016	64:DAW	68:read	69:2017-09-05	63:9780756408336	67:2/5	71:https://www.goodreads.com/book/show/26068046
5:000260811	6:gr-260811	3:God is Love: Deus Caritas Est	4:book review	60:God is Love: Deus Caritas Est	61:Pope Benedict XVI	62:2006	64:USCCB Publishing	68:read	69:2011-01-01	63:9781574557589	67:4/5	71:https://www.goodreads.com/book/show/260811
5:026082188	6:gr-26082188	3:The Dispatcher (The Dispatcher, #1)	4:book review	60:The Dispatcher (The Dispatcher, #1)	61:John Scalzi	62:2016	64:Audible Studios	68:read	69:2017-01-31	67:5/5	71:https://www.goodreads.com/book/show/26082188
5:026082916	6:gr-26082916	3:Ready Player Two (Ready Player One, #2)	4:book review	60:Ready Player Two (Ready Player One, #2)	61:Ernest Cline	62:2020	64:Ballantine Books	68:read	69:2021-01-20	63:9781524761332	67:2/5	70:Ready Player One was a story of an underdog against a megacorporation. It was an adventure romp through nostalgia, geekdom, and pop-culture that empowered the little guy. In retrospect the realities of that first book are fairly dark: that an incredibly unfair wealth disparity would continue to exist and this one lone figure would inherit it all based not on any actual merit, but because he out-shined the others in their absolute obssessive study and praise of a narcissistic programmer. There's so much there to be criticised and debated, but that layer comes later. First is the adventure-romp, later is the cultural criticism.\n\nReady Player Two is not that. By necessity our heroes are no longer the plucky underdogs. They are now the leaders of the impossibly gross monopoly that controls the lives of everyone on Earth. It is given to them to decide whether people are ready or not for a technological advancement that will clearly shift the nature of humanity. Since these misfits are just random gamer nerds it comes as no surprise that they force the decision without giving it any thought or study. Horribleness ensues.\n\nBy the time we reach the adventure plot our main character has been revealed to be emotionally stunted, petty, and immature. While that may be an interesting starting point for the plucky underdog to overcome this time he's the unfathombly rich guy in charge of literally everything. It's not charming. It's dark.\n\nWhen his actions lead to a life-or-death crisis for billions there's no doubt that it was his fault. The fact that he's left in the position to fix it doesn't make things better, but worse. As the model from the first book comes back into focus--jumping from geekdom to pop-culture reference--it is without any joy. There's a doom hanging over all of it. This isn't an adventure of a hero, but a slog where every delay could cost the lives of innocents. Each moment of joy the heroes experience comes at a real cost for the rest of humanity.\n\nThere are moments of interesting action, fun cultural references, colorful imagery, and comedic moments; but overall the tone of the book is crippled by the stunted emotional development of the hero and his poor decisions that have caused all the trouble. This book is cultural commentary first, adventure-romp second, and that just doesn't work for me.	71:https://www.goodreads.com/book/show/26082916
5:002610107	6:gr-2610107	3:Pawn Power in Chess (Dover Chess)	4:book review	60:Pawn Power in Chess (Dover Chess)	61:Hans Kmoch	62:1990	64:Dover Publications	68:read	69:2021-05-07	63:9780486264868	66:chess	67:5/5	71:https://www.goodreads.com/book/show/2610107
5:000261240	6:gr-261240	3:The Cask of Amontillado	4:book review	60:The Cask of Amontillado	61:Edgar Allan Poe	62:2009	64:BookSurge	68:read	63:9781594561863	67:3/5	71:https://www.goodreads.com/book/show/261240
5:026126631	6:gr-26126631	3:Witch Is When Life Got Complicated (A Witch P.I. Mystery, #2)	4:book review	60:Witch Is When Life Got Complicated (A Witch P.I. Mystery, #2)	61:Adele Abbott	62:2015	64:Implode Publishing Ltd	68:read	69:2021-01-02	67:3/5	70:This series is so light hearted and simple that it's been a pleasure to read over the last few days. I've been binging them at about 2 a day. There's not much to say about craft quality, though. Books 1-12 especially are quite rough and feel more like free writing at times than novels. Even so it's been fun to see the author improve as she goes and to see the cast of characters grow.	71:https://www.goodreads.com/book/show/26126631
5:026129731	6:gr-26129731	3:101 Zen Stories	4:book review	60:101 Zen Stories	61:Nyogen Senzaki	62:2013	64:Trout Lake Media	68:read	69:2015-12-05	67:3/5	71:https://www.goodreads.com/book/show/26129731
5:026131600	6:gr-26131600	3:The Ethics (Ethica Ordine Geometrico Demonstrata) by Benedict de Spinoza: The Ethics of Spinoza	4:book review	60:The Ethics (Ethica Ordine Geometrico Demonstrata) by Benedict de Spinoza: The Ethics of Spinoza	61:Baruch Spinoza	62:2011	64:Createspace Independent Publishing Platform	68:read	69:2022-02-21	63:9781461176909	67:2/5	70:Dense, pedantic, and suffers from endless induction of half-baked ideas. Still, I understand why it's a foundational writing in the field. I'm happy to move on from it and I'm looking forward to the many books that will rip this one apart with welcome criticism.	71:https://www.goodreads.com/book/show/26131600
