5:000028187	6:gr-28187	3:The Lightning Thief (Percy Jackson and the Olympians, #1)	4:book review	60:The Lightning Thief (Percy Jackson and the Olympians, #1)	61:Rick Riordan	62:2006	64:Disney Hyperion Books	68:read	69:2011-10-03	67:4/5	70:That was pretty great. I'm amazed that so much vital plot was changed for the movie. Maybe I shouldn't be surprised, though. Anyway, it's a really fun YA piece. I think I'll read the whole series really quick.	71:https://www.goodreads.com/book/show/28187
5:000028194	6:gr-28194	3:Inkheart (Inkworld, #1)	4:book review	60:Inkheart (Inkworld, #1)	61:Cornelia Funke	62:2005	64:Scholastic Paperbacks	68:read	69:2023-09-17	63:9780439709101	67:2/5	70:This book floundered in the middle quite a bit as if the author didn't really know where to take it next. The protagonists find themselves repeating their positions and the aims of the villains become muddy at best. There's a nice story in there somewhere, but I think we could trim about half this book away before we found it.	71:https://www.goodreads.com/book/show/28194
5:028233370	6:gr-28233370	3:Drysine Legacy (The Spiral Wars, #2)	4:book review	60:Drysine Legacy (The Spiral Wars, #2)	61:Joel Shepherd	62:2015	64:CreateSpace Publishing	68:read	69:2021-07-10	67:4/5	70:There's a lot going on here politically but the action pace remains high. Very good series so far.	71:https://www.goodreads.com/book/show/28233370
5:000028249	6:gr-28249	3:The Magicians' Guild (Black Magician Trilogy, #1)	4:book review	60:The Magicians' Guild (Black Magician Trilogy, #1)	61:Trudi Canavan	62:2004	64:Orbit	68:read	69:2013-01-05	63:9781841493138	67:2/5	70:This story was just okay. The first major plot point took over half the book to resolve when it should have taken 3 chapters at most. That really sums up why this book didn't earn another star or two from me. All in all, not a lot happens. I'm guessing if I finish the series, it will all add up to the content that would comfortably fill a single book. It's just a bit to leisurely written for me.	71:https://www.goodreads.com/book/show/28249
