5:028271109	6:gr-28271109	3:The 100X Life: 7 Simple Daily Habits That Will Transform Your Life, Unlock Your Greatest Potential, and Create a Life Beyond Your Wildest Dreams!	4:book review	60:The 100X Life: 7 Simple Daily Habits That Will Transform Your Life, Unlock Your Greatest Potential, and Create a Life Beyond Your Wildest Dreams!	61:Jennifer Harshman	62:2015	64:Stephen F. Skinner, RPh.	68:read	69:2017-01-15	67:1/5	71:https://www.goodreads.com/book/show/28271109
5:000002836	6:gr-2836	3:Bridge to Terabithia	4:book review	60:Bridge to Terabithia	61:Katherine Paterson	62:2008	64:HarperTeen	68:read	69:1995-01-01	63:9780060734015	67:5/5	71:https://www.goodreads.com/book/show/2836
5:028385685	6:gr-28385685	3:Free the Darkness (King's Dark Tidings, #1)	4:book review	60:Free the Darkness (King's Dark Tidings, #1)	61:Kel Kade	62:2015	64:Dark Rover Publishing, LLC	68:read	69:2017-11-18	67:2/5	70:The reviews are wrong on this one. Just like my complaints of Wise Man's Fear, we have another book about the adventures of The Perfect Warrior. Unlike the other series, we don't need to put up with the arrogance of an autobiography, but we are still presented with a character who has literally "mastered all the skills". \n\nEvery challenge is easily overcome. Everyone else is an amateur. Men envy him, women want him, and it is a testament to his perfection that he doesn't notice either.\n\nJust... *eyeroll*	71:https://www.goodreads.com/book/show/28385685
5:028464896	6:gr-28464896	3:Hell Divers (Hell Divers, #1)	4:book review	60:Hell Divers (Hell Divers, #1)	61:Nicholas Sansbury Smith	62:2016	64:Blackstone Audiobooks	68:read	69:2018-06-24	63:9781504713955	67:1/5	70:Everything is constantly the worst it could possibly be. There is no rising tension because the book starts at 100% and then stays there until the end. It's boring. I gave up with less than 30 pages remaining. I don't care how it ends.	71:https://www.goodreads.com/book/show/28464896
5:000028481	6:gr-28481	3:Dragon Wing (The Death Gate Cycle, #1)	4:book review	60:Dragon Wing (The Death Gate Cycle, #1)	61:Margaret Weis	62:1990	64:Spectra	68:read	69:1992-01-01	63:9780553286397	67:3/5	71:https://www.goodreads.com/book/show/28481
5:028488649	6:gr-28488649	3:The Melancholy of Resistance	4:book review	60:The Melancholy of Resistance	61:László Krasznahorkai	62:2016	64:Tuskar Rock	68:read	69:2022-05-28	63:9781781256244	67:3/5	70:What a wonderfully interesting book. It creates such feelings of dread and unease. The storyline is somewhat absurd and allegorical. There's so many layers going on it's quite impressive. I'm not sure how else to review it, though. I should note as a warning to readers that it's incredibly dense with sentences running half the length of a page on average. That may be a turn-off for many.	71:https://www.goodreads.com/book/show/28488649
