5:031921096	6:gr-31921096	3:Guardian of the Plundered Tomes (Black Ocean 4.5)	4:book review	60:Guardian of the Plundered Tomes (Black Ocean 4.5)	61:J.S. Morin	62:2015	68:read	69:2023-03-07	67:4/5	71:https://www.goodreads.com/book/show/31921096
5:000000320	6:gr-320	3:One Hundred Years of Solitude	4:book review	60:One Hundred Years of Solitude	61:Gabriel García Márquez	62:2003	64:Harper	68:read	69:2014-07-15	67:4/5	71:https://www.goodreads.com/book/show/320
5:003207249	6:gr-3207249	3:Pawn Sacrifice!: Winning at chess the adventurous way	4:book review	60:Pawn Sacrifice!: Winning at chess the adventurous way	61:Timothy W. Taylor	62:2008	64:Everyman Chess	68:read	69:2008-12-28	63:9781857445657	66:chess	67:4/5	70:This is one of the better chess books I've read. It's focused, the examples are thorough, but not overly technical or assuming. While the author does follow the tendency to spiral off into alternate lines at times without diagrams, generally speaking there are enough board diagrams of the main lines that you don't need to set up a chessboard while you read.	71:https://www.goodreads.com/book/show/3207249
5:032109569	6:gr-32109569	3:We Are Legion (We Are Bob) (Bobiverse, #1)	4:book review	60:We Are Legion (We Are Bob) (Bobiverse, #1)	61:Dennis E. Taylor	62:2016	64:Worldbuilders Press	68:read	69:2017-05-26	67:4/5	70:This is a really fun sci-fi book with a really unique angle. The story was engaging and interesting, but it started getting listless about halfway through. There's a few plots pulling the story along, but they're not very connected. Things end abruptly without much resolution.\n\nI'll read more in the series eventually.	71:https://www.goodreads.com/book/show/32109569
