5:032177852	6:gr-32177852	3:The Disappearance of Winter's Daughter  (The Riyria Chronicles, #4)	4:book review	60:The Disappearance of Winter's Daughter  (The Riyria Chronicles, #4)	61:Michael J. Sullivan	62:2018	64:Riyria Entprises LLC	68:read	69:2018-05-18	63:9781943363131	67:4/5	71:https://www.goodreads.com/book/show/32177852
5:032191710	6:gr-32191710	3:Astrophysics for People in a Hurry	4:book review	60:Astrophysics for People in a Hurry	61:Neil deGrasse Tyson	62:2017	64:W. W. Norton & Company	68:read	69:2018-05-26	63:9780393609394	67:4/5	71:https://www.goodreads.com/book/show/32191710
5:032199241	6:gr-32199241	3:Kantovan Vault (The Spiral Wars, #3)	4:book review	60:Kantovan Vault (The Spiral Wars, #3)	61:Joel Shepherd	62:2016	64:CreateSpace Publishing	68:read	69:2021-07-30	67:4/5	70:What a heist!\n\nThese books are a really interesting blend of highly political and highly action-packed, with a preference for close-in move-by-move sequences that draw you close to the battles. I'm really enjoying those but the political relationships and histories of thousands of years is what makes it special.	71:https://www.goodreads.com/book/show/32199241
5:003226758	6:gr-3226758	3:Real World Haskell	4:book review	60:Real World Haskell	61:Bryan O'Sullivan	62:2008	64:O'Reilly Media	68:read	69:2018-11-04	63:9780596514983	67:3/5	71:https://www.goodreads.com/book/show/3226758
5:003227063	6:gr-3227063	3:The Way of Shadows (Night Angel, #1)	4:book review	60:The Way of Shadows (Night Angel, #1)	61:Brent Weeks	62:2008	64:Orbit	68:read	69:2009-02-08	63:9780316033671	67:4/5	70:Brent Weeks's first book in the Night Angel series was a wonderfully engaging fantasy novel. He obviously comes from the George R. R. Martin school of writing and is thusly unafraid to maim or even kill his main characters. His characters are full and grow beautifully throughout the story, and more than one will surprise you. This is a great, quick read for someone looking for a good fantasy diversion.\n\nReread: This pass through the book left me with a few misgivings about character voice, some awkward relationship dialogue, and a rather convenient return of a villan that didn't really seem believable. Still, with all that, it's a good book. Read and enjoy.	71:https://www.goodreads.com/book/show/3227063
5:032283608	6:gr-32283608	3:Soulsmith (Cradle, #2)	4:book review	60:Soulsmith (Cradle, #2)	61:Will Wight	62:2016	64:Hidden Gnome Publishing	68:read	69:2020-03-24	67:4/5	71:https://www.goodreads.com/book/show/32283608
5:032306108	6:gr-32306108	3:Holiday Witch (Torrent Witches, #5)	4:book review	60:Holiday Witch (Torrent Witches, #5)	61:Tess Lake	62:2016	64:Tess Lake	68:read	69:2023-06-09	67:2/5	71:https://www.goodreads.com/book/show/32306108
5:032322052	6:gr-32322052	3:Meditation: The Journey Beyond the Mind	4:book review	60:Meditation: The Journey Beyond the Mind	61:Tai Morello	62:2016	68:read	69:2019-10-06	67:2/5	71:https://www.goodreads.com/book/show/32322052
5:003236307	6:gr-3236307	3:Graceling (Graceling Realm, #1)	4:book review	60:Graceling (Graceling Realm, #1)	61:Kristin Cashore	62:2008	64:Harcourt	68:read	69:2013-06-21	63:9780152063962	67:3/5	70:I was totally ready to rip this book apart in my review when halfway through, but some unexpected developments of character and plot changed my mind. The overall problem I had is the same that Felica Day hit upon in her review. Things seem too sketchy and not thought out throughout a lot of the book. Again and again I found myself yelling out loud, "The character wouldn't do that!", too. It was like after the plot was sketched out, Ms Cashore didn't think through the character's motivations and thoughts anymore.\n\nSo, as I said, at 50% the book was on par for a 2-star review. The pace picked up and--more importantly--the characters began to grow. The climb through the pass was especially good for this. Descriptions became more vibrant, history was revealed, and I didn't have to rely on just the basics of a story. By the end of the book I was interested in reading the sequel. Way to pull it out in the end.	71:https://www.goodreads.com/book/show/3236307
5:032507304	6:gr-32507304	3:The Wolf of the North (Wolf of the North #1)	4:book review	60:The Wolf of the North (Wolf of the North #1)	61:Duncan M. Hamilton	62:2016	68:read	69:2018-03-06	67:5/5	70:This is a fantastic execution of the familiar story of a protagonist growing from chubby useless kid to powerful warrior.	71:https://www.goodreads.com/book/show/32507304
