5:033412897	6:gr-33412897	3:Secondborn (Secondborn, #1)	4:book review	60:Secondborn (Secondborn, #1)	61:Amy A. Bartol	62:2017	64:47North	68:read	69:2017-09-11	63:9781542095020	67:2/5	71:https://www.goodreads.com/book/show/33412897
5:000334176	6:gr-334176	3:The Sparrow (The Sparrow, #1)	4:book review	60:The Sparrow (The Sparrow, #1)	61:Mary Doria Russell	62:1997	64:Ballantine Books	68:read	69:2009-01-01	63:9780449912553	67:4/5	71:https://www.goodreads.com/book/show/334176
5:033538688	6:gr-33538688	3:Scientific Secrets for Self-Control	4:book review	60:Scientific Secrets for Self-Control	61:C. Nathan DeWall	62:2013	64:The Great Courses	68:read	69:2015-12-25	67:2/5	70:This is a series of lectures from "The Great Courses". I listened to the Audible recording.\n\nThe author/lecturer is incredibly long winded and slow to his points. I had to listen at double speed to keep from losing patience, which is fitting for the subject matter discussed. The lectures spent a great deal of time reviewing experiments to illustrate points about the nature of Self-Control and its place in the brain. This was informative, but doled out in exceedingly greuling terms. The entire series of lectures lasts about three hours. If the author spoke naturally it would have been one hour.	71:https://www.goodreads.com/book/show/33538688
5:033555224	6:gr-33555224	3:Thunderhead (Arc of a Scythe, #2)	4:book review	60:Thunderhead (Arc of a Scythe, #2)	61:Neal Shusterman	62:2018	64:Simon & Schuster Books for Young Readers	68:read	69:2020-01-24	63:9781442472457	67:4/5	71:https://www.goodreads.com/book/show/33555224
