5:033803761	6:gr-33803761	3:Witch Is Why The Wolf Howled (A Witch P.I. Mystery #18)	4:book review	60:Witch Is Why The Wolf Howled (A Witch P.I. Mystery #18)	61:Adele Abbott	62:2017	64:Implode Publishing Ltd	68:read	69:2021-03-13	67:2/5	71:https://www.goodreads.com/book/show/33803761
5:033825757	6:gr-33825757	3:Paradox Bound	4:book review	60:Paradox Bound	61:Peter Clines	62:2017	64:Crown	68:read	69:2020-08-13	63:9780553418330	67:3/5	71:https://www.goodreads.com/book/show/33825757
5:003382663	6:gr-3382663	3:Doctor Who: The Story of Martha	4:book review	60:Doctor Who: The Story of Martha	61:Dan Abnett	62:2008	64:BBC Books	68:read	69:2013-11-19	63:9781846075612	67:4/5	70:Wonder what happened during Martha's year walking the Earth without the Doctor? Here you go! There's also some really good other side-stories. One of the best Doctor Who reads so far.	71:https://www.goodreads.com/book/show/3382663
5:003382664	6:gr-3382664	3:Doctor Who: The Eyeless	4:book review	60:Doctor Who: The Eyeless	61:Lance Parkin	62:2008	64:BBC Books	68:read	69:2014-05-04	63:9781846075629	67:3/5	71:https://www.goodreads.com/book/show/3382664
5:003382666	6:gr-3382666	3:Doctor Who: Beautiful Chaos	4:book review	60:Doctor Who: Beautiful Chaos	61:Gary Russell	62:2008	64:BBC Books	68:read	69:2014-04-18	63:9781846075636	67:2/5	71:https://www.goodreads.com/book/show/3382666
5:033838460	6:gr-33838460	3:Daughter of Dragons (The Legacy of Dragons, #1)	4:book review	60:Daughter of Dragons (The Legacy of Dragons, #1)	61:Jack Campbell	62:2017	64:Audible Studios	68:read	69:2017-12-10	67:1/5	70:The plot of this book is a rehash of the first series with characters that are a rehash from the first series. There's nothing new here. Above and beyond that, it's telling a story I really don't care to hear. There was so much potential of what Urth could bring to Dematr, but instead it's a repetitive and preachy criticism of the modern world.	71:https://www.goodreads.com/book/show/33838460
5:033869571	6:gr-33869571	3:Keystone (Crossbreed, #1; Mageriverse, #17)	4:book review	60:Keystone (Crossbreed, #1; Mageriverse, #17)	61:Dannika Dark	62:2017	64:Dannika Dark	68:read	69:2020-09-26	67:2/5	70:I was attracted to this book by the reviews and ratings. I figured with the genre and the vast quantity of books in the series (and by the album art) that this wasn't going to be deep reading. It's nice to have some fluff once in a while. The beginning of the book seemed to deliver, but then it sort of lost its way.\n\nThe point of the main group, Keystone, was vague and fluccuated between hit squad for the rich & powerful and freelance investigative unit. It sort of makes sense at any point in time, but over the course of the novel it seemed more and more ridiculous. The mysterious leadership of the breeds contracted out killings to this group when they couldn't prove guilt enough by normal means. But that same leadership group are the ones making the rules. Why pay this outside group to do this stuff, and why does this outside group randomly start caring about evidence and proof of guilt at odd times.\n\nThe characterizations are also pretty flat. I know that's to be expected, but with such a large cast I was hoping for a bit more. I never really got a good sense of who the main character, Raven Black, truly was. Her desires and motivations shifted from scene to scene. For someone who's been effectively homeless for five years I didn't get much of that vibe from her either.\n\nThe story itself was okay. The bad guy never seemed like a real threat. The challenges presented all seemed to have much simpler solutions than the characters chose. I don't think I'll be reading anything else in this series.	71:https://www.goodreads.com/book/show/33869571
5:033898471	6:gr-33898471	3:Champions of the Dragon (Epic Fallacy, #1)	4:book review	60:Champions of the Dragon (Epic Fallacy, #1)	61:Michael James Ploof	62:2017	64:Traveling Bard Publishing	68:read	69:2017-09-05	67:1/5	70:Pratchett, this is not.	71:https://www.goodreads.com/book/show/33898471
5:033917107	6:gr-33917107	3:On Tyranny: Twenty Lessons from the Twentieth Century	4:book review	60:On Tyranny: Twenty Lessons from the Twentieth Century	61:Timothy Snyder	62:2017	64:Tim Duggan Books	68:read	69:2018-10-27	63:9780804190114	67:3/5	70:There are excellent parallels to modern issues within these pages, but very little organizing principle. It begins as a warning on general terms and then quickly focuses on the American presidency. Overall the sentiment is good and the read is quick but there's not enough substance to my tastes.	71:https://www.goodreads.com/book/show/33917107
5:033947181	6:gr-33947181	3:Retro Version (Black Ocean #6)	4:book review	60:Retro Version (Black Ocean #6)	61:J.S. Morin	62:2015	64:Magical Scrivener	68:read	69:2023-03-07	63:9781939233745	67:4/5	71:https://www.goodreads.com/book/show/33947181
