5:000034268	6:gr-34268	3:Peter Pan	4:book review	60:Peter Pan	61:J.M. Barrie	62:2003	64:Henry Holt and Co.	68:read	69:2019-12-31	63:9780805072457	67:4/5	71:https://www.goodreads.com/book/show/34268
5:000342681	6:gr-342681	3:The Top Ten Mistakes Leaders Make	4:book review	60:The Top Ten Mistakes Leaders Make	61:Hans Finzel	62:2001	64:David C Cook	68:read	69:2007-01-01	63:9780781433655	67:3/5	71:https://www.goodreads.com/book/show/342681
5:034311452	6:gr-34311452	3:Year One (Chronicles of The One, #1)	4:book review	60:Year One (Chronicles of The One, #1)	61:Nora Roberts	62:2017	64:St. Martin's Press	68:read	69:2020-04-28	63:9781250122957	67:1/5	70:Ugh. The male characters all sounds exactly the same, excepting one that has an accent. There's no personality. I'm also pretty annoyed this plot went so quickly to "Americans have to figure out how to survive without shopping". How dreary and boring.	71:https://www.goodreads.com/book/show/34311452
5:034321278	6:gr-34321278	3:God Moments: Unexpected Encounters in the Ordinary	4:book review	60:God Moments: Unexpected Encounters in the Ordinary	61:Andy  Otto	62:2017	64:Ave Maria Press	68:read	69:2017-05-26	67:5/5	70:It was a joy to read this. Andy and I shared a room in the Jesuit novitiate years ago and shared many, many evenings discussing our faith and prayer experiences. This book took me back to that little house once again.\n\nAndy's stories come from his personal journey, but they speak to a broader experience of God that any of us can find. His earnestness and intimacy invite the reader to journey with him through both profound and mundane moments, and discover for themselves that the divine is everywhere.	71:https://www.goodreads.com/book/show/34321278
5:034324929	6:gr-34324929	3:Everyday Ethics	4:book review	60:Everyday Ethics	61:Dr Simon Longstaff	62:2017	64:Ventura Press	68:read	69:2022-04-16	63:9781925183559	67:2/5	70:The structure of this work was unbalanced, launching with a lot of personal anecdotes and then the world's fastest survey of the field before moving to individual issues in brief. I respect the idea of tying ethics to practicality, but I don't think this actually achieved the goal. It was left somewhere in between, neither educating, nor bridging academia to everyday life in a satisfying way.	71:https://www.goodreads.com/book/show/34324929
5:034327194	6:gr-34327194	3:Dungeon Madness (The Divine Dungeon, #2)	4:book review	60:Dungeon Madness (The Divine Dungeon, #2)	61:Dakota Krout	62:2017	64:Amazon Digital Services	68:read	69:2017-12-05	67:2/5	70:More of the same. I didn't really care about anyone or anything. No need to continue the series.	71:https://www.goodreads.com/book/show/34327194
5:034388144	6:gr-34388144	3:Love Witch (Torrent Witches, #7)	4:book review	60:Love Witch (Torrent Witches, #7)	61:Tess Lake	62:2017	64:Tess Lake	68:read	69:2023-06-17	67:3/5	71:https://www.goodreads.com/book/show/34388144
5:034403860	6:gr-34403860	3:Sufficiently Advanced Magic (Arcane Ascension, #1)	4:book review	60:Sufficiently Advanced Magic (Arcane Ascension, #1)	61:Andrew Rowe	62:2017	68:read	69:2017-11-30	67:4/5	70:This story is super fun! It's got dungeon diving, magic school, world building, and plenty of betrayal. I can't wait for the sequels.	71:https://www.goodreads.com/book/show/34403860
5:034455798	6:gr-34455798	3:The Wizards of Once (The Wizards of Once, #1)	4:book review	60:The Wizards of Once (The Wizards of Once, #1)	61:Cressida Cowell	62:2017	64:Hodder Children's Books	68:read	69:2019-02-26	63:9781444936704	67:3/5	70:The tone is so lovely. It reminds me a bit of the Girl Who Drank the Moon, but slightly sillier. The action is predictable, but it's self-referential enough to be forgiven. It is, afterall, a fairy tale. Unfortunately it didn't really connect with me on a deeper level. I don't have any specific faults to call out. I just liked it, didn't love it.	71:https://www.goodreads.com/book/show/34455798
