5:000034507	6:gr-34507	3:Equal Rites (Discworld, #3; Witches, #1)	4:book review	60:Equal Rites (Discworld, #3; Witches, #1)	61:Terry Pratchett	62:2005	64:Harper Perennial	68:read	69:2015-05-12	63:9780060855901	67:5/5	71:https://www.goodreads.com/book/show/34507
5:034521681	6:gr-34521681	3:Dominion of Blades (Dominion of Blades, #1)	4:book review	60:Dominion of Blades (Dominion of Blades, #1)	61:Matt Dinniman	62:2017	64:Dandy House	68:read	69:2022-12-10	67:3/5	70:It was fun but not worth continuing. The Wandering Inn set the genre bar high.	71:https://www.goodreads.com/book/show/34521681
5:034545741	6:gr-34545741	3:Witch Is Why The Music Stopped (A Witch P.I. Mystery #19)	4:book review	60:Witch Is Why The Music Stopped (A Witch P.I. Mystery #19)	61:Adele Abbott	62:2017	64:Implode Publishing Ltd	68:read	69:2021-03-13	67:2/5	70:Just more candy to cleanse the palette	71:https://www.goodreads.com/book/show/34545741
5:034630147	6:gr-34630147	3:Mission Inadvisable (Black Ocean, #13)	4:book review	60:Mission Inadvisable (Black Ocean, #13)	61:J.S. Morin	62:2017	64:Magical Scrivener Press	68:read	69:2023-03-07	63:1942642164	67:5/5	71:https://www.goodreads.com/book/show/34630147
5:034684622	6:gr-34684622	3:Leonardo da Vinci	4:book review	60:Leonardo da Vinci	61:Walter Isaacson	62:2017	64:Simon & Schuster	68:read	69:2018-01-27	63:9781501139154	67:5/5	71:https://www.goodreads.com/book/show/34684622
5:034703445	6:gr-34703445	3:Edgedancer (The Stormlight Archive, #2.5)	4:book review	60:Edgedancer (The Stormlight Archive, #2.5)	61:Brandon Sanderson	62:2017	64:Tor Books	68:read	69:2022-10-08	63:9781250166548	67:5/5	70:A whole novella of one of my favorite side characters in the series! YES PLEASE.\n\nLift is such a fun (awesome) character but her role in the main plot is just in passing. Here we get to explore some of her backstory, meet one of the cultures of Roshar which has been left in the background until now, and spend some time with a herald. It's a really fun story with plenty of humor, action, and insight.\n\nAs I mentioned with Dawnshard, the novellas to the Stormlight Archive are all worth reading. Do yourself the favor of checking this one out.	71:https://www.goodreads.com/book/show/34703445
5:034728667	6:gr-34728667	3:Children of Blood and Bone (Legacy of Orïsha, #1)	4:book review	60:Children of Blood and Bone (Legacy of Orïsha, #1)	61:Tomi Adeyemi	62:2018	64:Henry Holt Company	68:read	69:2020-09-01	63:9781250170972	67:2/5	70:DNF.\n\nI made it about halfway through this book before deciding to abandon it. I was bored. The characters didn't feel like they were going anywhere and the adventure seemed frivolous. I think the unfamiliar West-African roots of the mythology and accent of the reader (I did the audiobook) kept me engaged far longer than I would have been normally. I thought it was hiding something deeper and more interesting, but at its heart this feels like a rather generic Y/A fantasy.	71:https://www.goodreads.com/book/show/34728667
5:034736722	6:gr-34736722	3:Commune: Book One (Commune, #1)	4:book review	60:Commune: Book One (Commune, #1)	61:Joshua Gayou	62:2017	68:read	69:2018-10-03	67:4/5	70:I ended up cleaning out my bug-out bag and replacing some aging items thanks to this book. It was pretty solid and not too horrifying as far as armegeddon books go. I'll probably pick up book 2 once I give my wallet a break.	71:https://www.goodreads.com/book/show/34736722
5:034741771	6:gr-34741771	3:Jorundyr's Path (Wolf of the North, #2)	4:book review	60:Jorundyr's Path (Wolf of the North, #2)	61:Duncan M. Hamilton	62:2017	68:read	69:2018-03-17	67:3/5	70:Not as strong as the first book. Pacing was odd in places and there's a bit to much exposition. Overall it's still a good read	71:https://www.goodreads.com/book/show/34741771
5:003475161	6:gr-3475161	3:Turn Coat (The Dresden Files, #11)	4:book review	60:Turn Coat (The Dresden Files, #11)	61:Jim Butcher	62:2009	64:Roc	68:read	69:2010-01-01	63:9780451462565	67:5/5	71:https://www.goodreads.com/book/show/3475161
5:034794475	6:gr-34794475	3:Journal 29 (Journal 29, #1)	4:book review	60:Journal 29 (Journal 29, #1)	61:Dimitris Chassapakis	62:2017	64:Primedia eLaunch LLC	68:read	69:2018-01-01	63:9781635871722	67:5/5	71:https://www.goodreads.com/book/show/34794475
5:034828626	6:gr-34828626	3:A Place Called Perfect	4:book review	60:A Place Called Perfect	61:Helena Duggan	62:2017	64:Usborne	68:read	69:2021-10-31	63:9781474924160	67:2/5	71:https://www.goodreads.com/book/show/34828626
5:034840759	6:gr-34840759	3:The X-Files: Cold Cases (X-Files, #1)	4:book review	60:The X-Files: Cold Cases (X-Files, #1)	61:Joe Harris	62:2017	64:Audible Studios	68:read	69:2017-09-22	67:3/5	70:It was a bit more on the nose than the X-Files I remember. Also, the weird excuse to bring back all the old characters felt forced. Still Mulder and Scully, though, so still fun.	71:https://www.goodreads.com/book/show/34840759
5:034849019	6:gr-34849019	3:Ms. Marvel, Vol. 8: Mecca	4:book review	60:Ms. Marvel, Vol. 8: Mecca	61:G. Willow Wilson	62:2017	64:Marvel	68:read	69:2022-01-01	63:9781302906085	67:3/5	70:The best plot line in this series was the town turning against super-powered people, wanting to drive them out completely and take back control of Jersey City. Unfortunately it wasn't given enough time to fully explore the non-evil dimensions of that. The yellow ballcaps and ties to Hydra made it clear that despite having civilians in the movement that was going to be washed over in favor of a quick solve. Interestingly the judicial review and overturning of the problem could have happened without Ms. Marvel's involvement at all. Her presence escallated the issues and forced her to solve them.\n\nI would have loved a deeper look at how a literal power inequality (super heroes) creates untold problems for ordinary citizens. The distribution of powers, who gets to use them in a region, how they are put into practice, and what sort of review they have... this is Watchmen level discussion and it was nearly addressed here, but not quite. Even giving a single voice to a moderate civilian instead of the power-hungry mob would have given that more depth.\n\nRegardless of my criticism, I like the social stigma angle, the coming together of various communities, and the deep involvement of the imam. Ms. Marvel stories are a cut above the rest of this generation of Marvel heroes.	71:https://www.goodreads.com/book/show/34849019
5:034849261	6:gr-34849261	3:Keto Slow Cooker & One-Pot Meals: Over 100 Simple & Delicious Low-Carb, Paleo and Primal Recipes for Weight Loss and Better Health (Volume 4) (Keto for Your Life, 4)	4:book review	60:Keto Slow Cooker & One-Pot Meals: Over 100 Simple & Delicious Low-Carb, Paleo and Primal Recipes for Weight Loss and Better Health (Volume 4) (Keto for Your Life, 4)	61:Martina Šlajerová	62:2017	64:Fair Winds Press	68:read	69:2018-01-01	63:9781592337804	67:4/5	71:https://www.goodreads.com/book/show/34849261
