5:036373298	6:gr-36373298	3:Trail of Lightning (The Sixth World, #1)	4:book review	60:Trail of Lightning (The Sixth World, #1)	61:Rebecca Roanhorse	62:2018	64:Saga Press	68:read	69:2019-06-04	63:9781534413498	67:3/5	71:https://www.goodreads.com/book/show/36373298
5:036418893	6:gr-36418893	3:Eternity or Bust (Black Ocean, #16)	4:book review	60:Eternity or Bust (Black Ocean, #16)	61:J.S. Morin	62:2017	64:Magical Scrivener Press	68:read	69:2023-03-07	63:1942642598	67:5/5	71:https://www.goodreads.com/book/show/36418893
5:036452106	6:gr-36452106	3:Fate of the Fallen (The Shroud of Prophecy, #1)	4:book review	60:Fate of the Fallen (The Shroud of Prophecy, #1)	61:Kel Kade	62:2019	64:Tor Books	68:read	69:2020-05-26	63:9781250293800	67:4/5	70:I really enjoyed the way this story seems to disrupt and play with the ideas of prophecy, but it's the sharp characterization that really drew me in. I'll have to pick up the next in the series.	71:https://www.goodreads.com/book/show/36452106
5:036505519	6:gr-36505519	3:Rendezvous with Rama (Rama, #1)	4:book review	60:Rendezvous with Rama (Rama, #1)	61:Arthur C. Clarke	62:2012	64:RosettaBooks	68:read	69:2018-01-01	67:5/5	71:https://www.goodreads.com/book/show/36505519
5:036542226	6:gr-36542226	3:Zero Hour (Expeditionary Force, #5)	4:book review	60:Zero Hour (Expeditionary Force, #5)	61:Craig Alanson	62:2017	68:read	69:2018-10-26	67:5/5	71:https://www.goodreads.com/book/show/36542226
5:036590798	6:gr-36590798	3:Icelandic Language: Texts in Icelandic	4:book review	60:Icelandic Language: Texts in Icelandic	61:Baldur Hilmarsson	62:2016	64:CreateSpace Independent Publishing Platform	68:read	69:2023-12-03	63:9781530454020	67:2/5	70:This practice texts collection follows a different strategy than the last one I read. Rather than focusing on language at a certain level of difficulty and letting you decypher vocabulary meaning in context it tries to frame a bunch of new vocabulary by subject and introduce a text that utiziles it all. The result isn't great. The grammar is all over the map in complexity and these brand new words you're learning may show up in any number of declanations adding to the difficulty. If you're more advanced at learning and just looking for a vocab dump, maybe this will serve you better.	71:https://www.goodreads.com/book/show/36590798
5:036597248	6:gr-36597248	3:The Stoic Body: An Ancient Twist To Modern Health	4:book review	60:The Stoic Body: An Ancient Twist To Modern Health	61:Philip Ghezelbash	62:2017	68:read	69:2018-01-01	67:3/5	71:https://www.goodreads.com/book/show/36597248
5:036611340	6:gr-36611340	3:Arduino: No Experience Required	4:book review	60:Arduino: No Experience Required	61:Ned Lee	62:2017	68:read	69:2018-02-03	67:3/5	71:https://www.goodreads.com/book/show/36611340
5:036611609	6:gr-36611609	3:Lost Witch (Torrent Witches, #9)	4:book review	60:Lost Witch (Torrent Witches, #9)	61:Tess Lake	62:2017	64:Tess Lake	68:read	69:2023-06-29	67:2/5	70:Lots of big things happened but they didn't land. Too much to quickly and too rushed. Honestly we had more depth in the reunion scene than the climax.	71:https://www.goodreads.com/book/show/36611609
5:036625952	6:gr-36625952	3:Wicked Witch (Torrent Witches, #10)	4:book review	60:Wicked Witch (Torrent Witches, #10)	61:Tess Lake	62:2017	64:Tess Lake	68:read	69:2023-07-01	67:4/5	70:The series ends with a bang, and a big step-up in writing. Where the previous books displayed little patience in main plotlines, often introducing a new twist situation only briefly before resolving it immediately, Wicked Witch picked up on the meta-plots hiding as background elements in the previous books. Not only this, but we're introduced to a new mystery at the start of this book based on events at the end of book 9, which leaves readers wondering, "Hey, what about X?" for quite a while before letting us in on the secret.\n\nTess Lake has shown she's capable of pacing her plots, letting the anxiety simmer, and ultimately paying off some long-term planning. I do wish there was more of it throughout the series, but even so this is a nice reward for those who stuck with the series for the whole run.	71:https://www.goodreads.com/book/show/36625952
5:036642458	6:gr-36642458	3:Skyward (Skyward, #1)	4:book review	60:Skyward (Skyward, #1)	61:Brandon Sanderson	62:2018	64:Gollancz	68:read	69:2019-01-06	63:9781473217850	67:5/5	71:https://www.goodreads.com/book/show/36642458
