5:048611323	6:gr-48611323	3:For Old Time's Sake (Black Ocean, #16.5)	4:book review	60:For Old Time's Sake (Black Ocean, #16.5)	61:J.S. Morin	68:read	69:2023-03-07	67:4/5	71:https://www.goodreads.com/book/show/48611323
5:048614029	6:gr-48614029	3:Dawn of X, Vol. 1	4:book review	60:Dawn of X, Vol. 1	61:Jonathan Hickman	62:2020	64:Marvel	68:read	69:2022-10-08	63:9781302921569	67:2/5	70:I haven't read X-Men in a long time and I heard good things about this series. It's just as disjointed and cryptic as I remember. If you don't follow every storyline of every character for decades then you're left guessing at key moments, references fail to land, and everything just feels like noise. We're two decades into the twenty-first century and these characters have a new homeland where they can be themselves and at peace, but they still wear their costumes and uniforms. Needless to say, I wasn't impressed.	71:https://www.goodreads.com/book/show/48614029
