5:050997900	6:gr-50997900	3:Asatru: A Beginner's Guide to the Heathen Path	4:book review	60:Asatru: A Beginner's Guide to the Heathen Path	61:Erin Lale	62:2020	64:Weiser Books	68:read	69:2021-09-14	67:3/5	70:The author is a community manager for Ásatrú on Facebook and this book benefits from her experience. It is well organised and approaches the subject logically without trying to persuade. I’ve no complaints. I feel better equipped to have conversations about Ásatrú and engage with practitioners here in Iceland.	71:https://www.goodreads.com/book/show/50997900
5:051057191	6:gr-51057191	3:Jade Legacy (The Green Bone Saga, #3)	4:book review	60:Jade Legacy (The Green Bone Saga, #3)	61:Fonda Lee	62:2021	64:Orbit	68:read	69:2023-02-10	63:9780356510590	67:5/5	71:https://www.goodreads.com/book/show/51057191
5:000005107	6:gr-5107	3:The Catcher in the Rye	4:book review	60:The Catcher in the Rye	61:J.D. Salinger	62:2001	64:Back Bay Books	68:read	69:2008-01-01	63:9780316769174	67:5/5	71:https://www.goodreads.com/book/show/5107
5:051077525	6:gr-51077525	3:Advanced Player’s Guide (Pathfinder 2nd Edition)	4:book review	60:Advanced Player’s Guide (Pathfinder 2nd Edition)	61:Logan Bonner	62:2020	64:Paizo Inc.	68:read	69:2022-07-17	63:9781640782570	67:5/5	71:https://www.goodreads.com/book/show/51077525
5:051083937	6:gr-51083937	3:The Brightest Shadow (The Brightest Shadow, #1)	4:book review	60:The Brightest Shadow (The Brightest Shadow, #1)	61:Sarah Lin	62:2020	64:Sarah Lin	68:read	69:2023-12-05	67:2/5	70:This started strong with some interesting world building and politics between various groups and factions. When "the hero" first showed up I thought we were in a turn for progress, but it became the exact opposite. The characters were all mired in the foggy reality of the hero's presence and stopped being the forces driving the plot. Quickly things became a slog.\n\nI didn't have enough time with the main characters to develop a true empathy for them or their plight, and then the spent forever acting not like themselves. It was hard to know if I should care at all. In the end, I didn't.\n\nThis story has strong roots, as Mr Miyagi would say. The author has a good command of her craft as well. I think where this failed for me is in the places where a strong editor would have been helpful. It needed some big pacing revisions, perhaps a bit of chapter reordering, some condensing, or maybe some expanding to break up the long stretches. Ultimately I wanted to feel like the characters actions made the story progress. If it's not them making things happen we have the wrong POV and this story should be about someone else.	71:https://www.goodreads.com/book/show/51083937
