5:059916652	6:gr-59916652	3:Warden	4:book review	60:Warden	61:Delyth Angharad	62:2021	64:Delyth Angharad	68:read	69:2022-03-08	67:4/5	70:This was a sweet romance in a fantasy setting. It's a gentle story with a very natural progression of the romantic interest, but there are still some fun thrilling moments of danger and action. I especially enjoyed the harpy encounter.	71:https://www.goodreads.com/book/show/59916652
5:000000006	6:gr-6	3:Harry Potter and the Goblet of Fire (Harry Potter, #4)	4:book review	60:Harry Potter and the Goblet of Fire (Harry Potter, #4)	61:J.K. Rowling	62:2002	64:Scholastic	68:read	69:2006-01-01	67:2/5	71:https://www.goodreads.com/book/show/6
5:060018635	6:gr-60018635	3:The Very Secret Society of Irregular Witches	4:book review	60:The Very Secret Society of Irregular Witches	61:Sangu Mandanna	62:2022	64:Berkley	68:read	69:2023-07-03	63:9780593439357	67:4/5	70:Adorable and cozy, and also well written.	71:https://www.goodreads.com/book/show/60018635
5:060070352	6:gr-60070352	3:The Story of Human Language (The Great Courses)	4:book review	60:The Story of Human Language (The Great Courses)	61:John McWhorter	62:2013	64:The Great Courses	68:read	69:2022-06-03	67:4/5	70:I really liked this course and feel like I learned so much. Language is endlessly fascinating. I can't say I deeply absorbed even half of what was presented, but I will take away some challenges to long held misunderstandings of how language works, and challenges to my own biases toward the evolution of English. I recommend this to any nerds out there.	71:https://www.goodreads.com/book/show/60070352
5:060288155	6:gr-60288155	3:Portal to Nova Roma	4:book review	60:Portal to Nova Roma	61:J.R.  Mathews	62:2022	68:read	69:2023-01-22	67:1/5	70:This is just awful. Super-AI main character that just wins at everything despite being an idiot somehow. The audible reader is boring and the author has a lot of craft development to do.	71:https://www.goodreads.com/book/show/60288155
5:000060400	6:gr-60400	3:The Ruins of Gorlan (Ranger's Apprentice, #1)	4:book review	60:The Ruins of Gorlan (Ranger's Apprentice, #1)	61:John Flanagan	62:2006	64:Puffin Books	68:read	69:2021-09-02	63:9780142406632	67:3/5	70:The book went predictibly and smoothly. I enjoyed the characters and the feel-good resolutions are a nice change from all the gritty stuff out there today. I'll keep going in the series.	71:https://www.goodreads.com/book/show/60400
5:006050668	6:gr-6050668	3:Doctor Who: The Nemonite Invasion	4:book review	60:Doctor Who: The Nemonite Invasion	61:David Roden	62:2009	64:BBC Audio	68:read	69:2014-05-04	63:9781408406793	67:3/5	71:https://www.goodreads.com/book/show/6050668
