5:000060510	6:gr-60510	3:Poison Study (Study, #1)	4:book review	60:Poison Study (Study, #1)	61:Maria V. Snyder	62:2007	64:Mira	68:read	69:2001-01-01	63:9780778324331	67:3/5	71:https://www.goodreads.com/book/show/60510
5:060525437	6:gr-60525437	3:The Wandering Inn: Book 6 - The General of Izril (The Wandering Inn, #4, Part 2)	4:book review	60:The Wandering Inn: Book 6 - The General of Izril (The Wandering Inn, #4, Part 2)	61:Pirateaba	62:2022	68:read	69:2022-05-10	67:5/5	70:*sniffle*	71:https://www.goodreads.com/book/show/60525437
5:060531410	6:gr-60531410	3:The Frugal Wizard’s Handbook for Surviving Medieval England	4:book review	60:The Frugal Wizard’s Handbook for Surviving Medieval England	61:Brandon Sanderson	62:2023	64:Dragonsteel Entertainment	68:read	69:2023-05-05	63:9781938570339	67:2/5	70:The story itself has a few interesting ideas, and the setting was pretty cool, but the plot didn't move me, and the interludes felt out of place with the tone. The ending was fun but also kind of a let down. My bar for a Sanderson story is quite high these days and this didn't do it for me.	71:https://www.goodreads.com/book/show/60531410
5:060531416	6:gr-60531416	3:Yumi and the Nightmare Painter	4:book review	60:Yumi and the Nightmare Painter	61:Brandon Sanderson	62:2023	64:Dragonsteel Entertainment	68:read	69:2023-08-13	63:9781938570377	67:4/5	71:https://www.goodreads.com/book/show/60531416
5:060531420	6:gr-60531420	3:The Sunlit Man (The Cosmere)	4:book review	60:The Sunlit Man (The Cosmere)	61:Brandon Sanderson	62:2023	64:Dragonsteel Entertainment	68:read	69:2023-10-16	63:9781938570391	67:4/5	70:A western-vibe in this Cosmere novel. It pushes backstory forward and fills in some gaps around the nature of investiture. The plot is pretty simple: a wanderer stumbles into a local problem. This was my second favorite of the 4 secret novels Brandon wrote during covid. Well worth the read.	71:https://www.goodreads.com/book/show/60531420
5:060617202	6:gr-60617202	3:The Variants	4:book review	60:The Variants	61:Gail Simone	62:2023	64:Marvel Universe	68:read	69:2023-04-11	63:9781302947064	67:2/5	71:https://www.goodreads.com/book/show/60617202
5:060718938	6:gr-60718938	3:Ceephay Queen (The Spiral Wars, #8)	4:book review	60:Ceephay Queen (The Spiral Wars, #8)	61:Joel Shepherd	62:2022	68:read	69:2022-11-26	67:4/5	70:AIs collide!	71:https://www.goodreads.com/book/show/60718938
5:006083231	6:gr-6083231	3:Etiquette	4:book review	60:Etiquette	61:Emily Post	62:1922	68:read	69:2014-01-01	67:3/5	71:https://www.goodreads.com/book/show/6083231
5:060851520	6:gr-60851520	3:The Wandering Inn: Book 7 - The Rains of Liscor (The Wandering Inn, #5, Part 1)	4:book review	60:The Wandering Inn: Book 7 - The Rains of Liscor (The Wandering Inn, #5, Part 1)	61:Pirateaba	62:2022	64:Podium Audio	68:read	69:2022-08-10	67:5/5	70:It's so hard to wait for the audio books when I know the written story is so far ahead. It's worth it though.	71:https://www.goodreads.com/book/show/60851520
5:060874817	6:gr-60874817	3:Match Game (Expeditionary Force, #14)	4:book review	60:Match Game (Expeditionary Force, #14)	61:Craig Alanson	62:2022	68:read	69:2022-07-06	67:5/5	70:I called it!!! Halfway through I figured out the shenanigans. Yay me!\n\nCan't wait for the next one. Lovely cliffhanger once again	71:https://www.goodreads.com/book/show/60874817
5:060888209	6:gr-60888209	3:Beware of Chicken (Beware of Chicken, #1)	4:book review	60:Beware of Chicken (Beware of Chicken, #1)	61:CasualFarmer	62:2022	64:Podium Publishing	68:read	69:2022-09-08	63:9781039413993	67:5/5	70:In the last couple years I've discovered the Xianxia Cultivation novels as a genre and become hooked, at least on the modern ones in English. The Cradle series, A Thousand Li, and so on, are all wonderful stories that scratch a particular itch. Enter "Beware of Chicken". This novel is a fantastic spoof of the tropes of the genre while simultaneously fulfilling its best parts. This story is a wonderful relaxing journey of putting down roots. The writing is great, the understanding of the genre is clearly top-notch, and the characters are a joy.\n\nI'm listening to this on audio and I can't wait for the second novel to be released in that form.\n\nIf you're a fan of cultivation novels you will absolutely love this. If you're new to the genre, put this one off until you've taken in some of the regular stories so you can really enjoy the way this bucks the trends.	71:https://www.goodreads.com/book/show/60888209
5:006089739	6:gr-6089739	3:SQL in a Nutshell: A Desktop Quick Reference Guide (In a Nutshell (O'Reilly))	4:book review	60:SQL in a Nutshell: A Desktop Quick Reference Guide (In a Nutshell (O'Reilly))	61:Kevin E. Kline	62:2008	64:O'Reilly Media	68:read	69:2011-05-04	63:9780596518844	67:2/5	71:https://www.goodreads.com/book/show/6089739
5:006095331	6:gr-6095331	3:Summer's Path	4:book review	60:Summer's Path	61:Scott Blum	62:2009	64:Hay House	68:read	69:2018-09-16	67:2/5	70:The author tried shoving a lot into this short story but they didn't all fit right. Details stand out, characters don't. The elements that feel pulled in from life do more to highlight the falseness of the rest rather than grounding things. Meh.	71:https://www.goodreads.com/book/show/6095331
5:006101718	6:gr-6101718	3:The Magicians (The Magicians, #1)	4:book review	60:The Magicians (The Magicians, #1)	61:Lev Grossman	62:2009	64:Viking	68:read	69:2017-05-22	63:9780670020553	67:1/5	71:https://www.goodreads.com/book/show/6101718
5:061160984	6:gr-61160984	3:The Third Kingdom (A Thousand Li #7)	4:book review	60:The Third Kingdom (A Thousand Li #7)	61:Tao Wong	62:2022	64:Starlit Publishing	68:read	69:2022-07-20	67:4/5	70:Ooooh, a mystery!	71:https://www.goodreads.com/book/show/61160984
5:000061179	6:gr-61179	3:Ringworld (Ringworld, #1)	4:book review	60:Ringworld (Ringworld, #1)	61:Larry Niven	62:2005	64:Gollancz	68:read	69:2022-08-10	63:9780575077027	67:2/5	70:The author is most interested in telling us about his cool ideas for a massive ring world and much less interested in telling a story.	71:https://www.goodreads.com/book/show/61179
5:061184540	6:gr-61184540	3:Self Help	4:book review	60:Self Help	61:Ben H. Winters	62:2022	64:Audible Originals	68:read	69:2022-06-18	67:4/5	70:This audible original was funny, fast paced, and had a punchy ending. Great voice work from Wil Wheaton and Ron Perlman. Some nice audiobook self-referencing humor too. Definitely worth the quick listen.	71:https://www.goodreads.com/book/show/61184540
5:006120349	6:gr-6120349	3:Locke & Key, Vol. 2: Head Games	4:book review	60:Locke & Key, Vol. 2: Head Games	61:Joe Hill	62:2015	64:IDW Publishing	68:read	69:2021-05-22	67:3/5	71:https://www.goodreads.com/book/show/6120349
5:006137154	6:gr-6137154	3:Fire (Graceling Realm, #2)	4:book review	60:Fire (Graceling Realm, #2)	61:Kristin Cashore	62:2009	64:Dial Books	68:read	69:2013-06-24	63:9780803734616	67:2/5	70:Graceling was in danger of a low review for most of the book until a pretty solid ending changed my mind. Fire had so much going against it from the start that it had no chance of recovery. I didn't completely hate it, but it was exceedingly uninteresting. I'll just touch on a couple things of note.\n\nA few good things:\n\nKristin Cashore is a decent writer. By that I mean she is able to describe a scene, write dialog, create a sense of movement, and all the other technical things a writer should be able to do. She also has some interesting ideas for what could make a Fantasy story compelling. Graces, Monsters, neat ideas.\n\nSome bad things:\n\nKristin Cashore is not a very good storyteller. Or maybe she only has one story in her, and needs to give us a variety of versions of it. Fire was, for all intensive purposes, the exact same story as Graceling. If you were to reduce it to an outline and character sketches it would be quite obvious.\n\nFinally, I feel wrong not mentioning the extreme imbalance in sexual power she gives her characters. I'm all for a historically portrayed low-fantasy where women face the struggles of history. This wasn't that. This was something else entirely, and it's a bit disturbing. I can't recommend young readers to this novel in much the same way as I can't recommend Piers Anthony's [b:A Spell for Chameleon|76664|A Spell for Chameleon (Xanth, #1)|Piers Anthony|http://d.gr-assets.com/books/1357166716s/76664.jpg|2501416].	71:https://www.goodreads.com/book/show/6137154
5:000614558	6:gr-614558	3:Dragon Harper (Pern, #19)	4:book review	60:Dragon Harper (Pern, #19)	61:Anne McCaffrey	62:2007	64:Del Rey	68:read	69:2003-01-01	63:9780345480309	67:4/5	71:https://www.goodreads.com/book/show/614558
5:006148028	6:gr-6148028	3:Catching Fire (The Hunger Games, #2)	4:book review	60:Catching Fire (The Hunger Games, #2)	61:Suzanne Collins	62:2009	64:Scholastic Press	68:read	69:2011-11-14	63:9780439023498	67:3/5	70:Quite a fun sequel. I'm really looking forward to reading Mockingjay.\n\nThis was my first Kindle Lending Library book. As soon as I finished it, I went back to Amazon to see if I could read Mockingjay, but it turns out there's a limit to how many you can check out each month. I guess I'll have to wait until December to finish the series.	71:https://www.goodreads.com/book/show/6148028
5:061553350	6:gr-61553350	3:Pathfinder Adventure Path: Abomination Vaults	4:book review	60:Pathfinder Adventure Path: Abomination Vaults	61:James Jacobs	62:2022	64:Paizo Inc.	68:read	69:2023-10-30	63:9781640784109	67:5/5	70:This is great. Loving the materials and the flexibility.	71:https://www.goodreads.com/book/show/61553350
