5:006186357	6:gr-6186357	3:The Maze Runner (The Maze Runner, #1)	4:book review	60:The Maze Runner (The Maze Runner, #1)	61:James Dashner	62:2009	64:Delacorte Press	68:read	63:9780385737944	67:2/5	71:https://www.goodreads.com/book/show/6186357
5:061880401	6:gr-61880401	3:The Wandering Inn: Book 8 - Blood of Liscor (The Wandering Inn, #5, Part 2)	4:book review	60:The Wandering Inn: Book 8 - Blood of Liscor (The Wandering Inn, #5, Part 2)	61:Pirateaba	62:2022	68:read	69:2022-12-07	67:5/5	71:https://www.goodreads.com/book/show/61880401
5:061885029	6:gr-61885029	3:Starter Villain	4:book review	60:Starter Villain	61:John Scalzi	62:2023	64:Tor Books	68:read	69:2023-10-10	63:9780765389220	67:4/5	70:What a fun little not-quite-villain story. And the cats!! Highly enjoyable read. No notes.	71:https://www.goodreads.com/book/show/61885029
5:000061886	6:gr-61886	3:The Curse of Chalion (World of the Five Gods, #1)	4:book review	60:The Curse of Chalion (World of the Five Gods, #1)	61:Lois McMaster Bujold	62:2003	64:Voyager	68:read	69:2011-05-30	63:9780007133611	67:5/5	70:I loved it. How's that for a review?\n\nOk, a few other notes. To those who will try to read it, don't go in expecting some classic high fantasy. This book has no dragons or epic quests, well at least not of the typical hero journey variety. It has been compared to Jane Austin and quite aptly. This is a story about people, about courts, about relationships, blood, titles, hopes and survival. The characters all have a wonderful firmness to them. One might say--if I venture an inside joke for those who have read it--they are all made of matter.\n\nRead it and enjoy the smile it leaves you in the end.	71:https://www.goodreads.com/book/show/61886
