5:062214893	6:gr-62214893	3:Travel by Bullet (The Dispatcher, #3)	4:book review	60:Travel by Bullet (The Dispatcher, #3)	61:John Scalzi	62:2022	64:Audible Originals	68:read	69:2022-09-11	67:4/5	70:A wonderful return to this universe. Crypto currency and the pandemic have changed the reality of the Dispatcher and this novela does a nice job exploring it. Excellent narration from Zachary Quinto.	71:https://www.goodreads.com/book/show/62214893
5:062227643	6:gr-62227643	3:Tröll, Álfar, Hestar: 3 Magical Short Stories Inspired by Iceland	4:book review	60:Tröll, Álfar, Hestar: 3 Magical Short Stories Inspired by Iceland	61:S.J.C. Schreiber	62:2022	68:read	69:2022-10-08	67:5/5	70:This short work is a collection of three lovely stories of reality touched by something a bit more. The Iceland setting and creatures of local myth are a perfect blending for experiences that edge beyond the day-to-day.\n\nThe writing is crisp and clear with a strong sense of character even in the brief pages. I especially loved the twist on the theme of finding lost things in the second story.\n\nIf you're looking for a quick read that hits at the essence of magical Iceland this is a good pick.	71:https://www.goodreads.com/book/show/62227643
5:000622855	6:gr-622855	3:A Murder of Quality (George Smiley, #2)	4:book review	60:A Murder of Quality (George Smiley, #2)	61:John le Carré	62:2002	64:Scribner	68:read	69:2022-10-07	63:9780743431682	67:3/5	71:https://www.goodreads.com/book/show/622855
5:000062291	6:gr-62291	3:A Storm of Swords (A Song of Ice and Fire, #3)	4:book review	60:A Storm of Swords (A Song of Ice and Fire, #3)	61:George R.R. Martin	62:2003	64:Bantam	68:read	69:2011-08-29	63:9780553573428	67:4/5	70:Best so far, for sure. I hear #4 is slow, but I smell good things coming.	71:https://www.goodreads.com/book/show/62291
5:006238735	6:gr-6238735	3:Incidents in the Life of a Slave Girl	4:book review	60:Incidents in the Life of a Slave Girl	61:Harriet Ann Jacobs	62:1861	68:read	69:2014-01-01	67:3/5	71:https://www.goodreads.com/book/show/6238735
5:006240539	6:gr-6240539	3:Redemption Alley (Jill Kismet, #3)	4:book review	60:Redemption Alley (Jill Kismet, #3)	61:Lilith Saintcrow	62:2009	64:Orbit	68:read	69:2022-09-04	63:9780316035460	67:4/5	70:The third book in the Jill Kismet series went to some gross places. When a friend asks Jill to look into a mundane crime she's not thrilled but takes it on reluctantly. When things on the nightside heat up suddenly the combo has people trying to kill her multiple times a day, and nearly succeeding. The action follows the spider web and not everything turns out okay in the end. It's the gritty reality of a hunter, and part of the charm of the series.	71:https://www.goodreads.com/book/show/6240539
5:006268088	6:gr-6268088	3:Leonardo's Notebooks	4:book review	60:Leonardo's Notebooks	61:Leonardo da Vinci	62:1519	68:read	69:1994-01-01	67:5/5	71:https://www.goodreads.com/book/show/6268088
5:062873999	6:gr-62873999	3:Translation State	4:book review	60:Translation State	61:Ann Leckie	62:2023	64:Orbit	68:read	69:2023-07-25	63:9780316289719	67:5/5	70:Absolutely fantastic. Ann Leckie brings a strong story with vibrant characters and further establishes detailed world building in the Imperial Radch universe. This story centers closely on the Presgr Translators. They're fascinating, alien and yet not. \n\nI wouldn't recommend starting with this book though. Do the Ancillary Justice series first. Provenance spoilers in here as well.	71:https://www.goodreads.com/book/show/62873999
5:000006288	6:gr-6288	3:The Road	4:book review	60:The Road	61:Cormac McCarthy	62:2006	64:Alfred A. Knopf	68:read	69:2008-11-23	63:9780307265432	67:2/5	70:Honestly, as much as I liked or didn't like the story, his choices in formatting severely hurt my enjoyment of the book. I understand it was an artistic choice to not separate dialogue or use quotation marks, just as I understand the lack of chapters. The reasons behind it aren't all that difficult to figure out. However, I believe that those choices, rather than give extra depth to the story, instead kept me from escaping into it. I was always behind the page, never engaging in the characters or emotionally investing.\n\nIf you are the type of reader who enjoys books that break writing conventions then maybe this is for you. I just wish I could have spent more energy on the story and less on the formatting.	71:https://www.goodreads.com/book/show/6288
5:062917275	6:gr-62917275	3:New Horizons (Beneath the Dragoneye Moons, #8)	4:book review	60:New Horizons (Beneath the Dragoneye Moons, #8)	61:Selkie Myth	62:2022	68:read	69:2023-03-25	67:3/5	70:I'm not really into the developments here. It felt really forced and I had a lot of questions regarding Elaine's motivations and her willingness to be separated from her friends. Still, story progresses. A bit repetitive and the lengthy school segments on biomancy specifics got tiresome. I don't think this series needed a magic school episode.	71:https://www.goodreads.com/book/show/62917275
5:006306050	6:gr-6306050	3:The Backyard Homestead: Produce All the Food You Need on Just a Quarter Acre!	4:book review	60:The Backyard Homestead: Produce All the Food You Need on Just a Quarter Acre!	61:Carleen Madigan	62:2009	64:Storey Publishing, LLC	68:read	69:2012-06-07	63:9781603421386	67:4/5	71:https://www.goodreads.com/book/show/6306050
5:063068384	6:gr-63068384	3:Tress of the Emerald Sea	4:book review	60:Tress of the Emerald Sea	61:Brandon Sanderson	62:2023	64:Tor Books	68:read	69:2023-11-14	63:9781250899651	67:5/5	70:Oh, I somehow missed rating this a few months back. I think this was my favorite of the secret novels. They each had their charms, but something about the characters and struggles in this one really felt special.\n\nAnyway, that's probably not a helpful review. Um, if you like Sanderson stuff, read this. It's good.	71:https://www.goodreads.com/book/show/63068384
5:006307034	6:gr-6307034	3:The Sandman: The Dream Hunters	4:book review	60:The Sandman: The Dream Hunters	61:Neil Gaiman	62:2009	64:Vertigo	68:read	69:2014-01-01	63:9781401224240	67:3/5	71:https://www.goodreads.com/book/show/6307034
5:000006310	6:gr-6310	3:Charlie and the Chocolate Factory (Charlie Bucket, #1)	4:book review	60:Charlie and the Chocolate Factory (Charlie Bucket, #1)	61:Roald Dahl	62:2005	64:Puffin Books	68:read	69:2008-01-01	63:9780142403884	67:4/5	71:https://www.goodreads.com/book/show/6310
5:000631233	6:gr-631233	3:Wizard's Bane (Wiz, #1)	4:book review	60:Wizard's Bane (Wiz, #1)	61:Rick Cook	62:1989	64:Baen Books	68:read	69:2012-07-13	63:9780671698034	67:3/5	70:It was a little strange mixing 80s computer programming with a fantasy series but it was a fun read. I wouldn't recommend this series unless you also have a geeky love of coding because, honestly, beyond that quirk it's not really that good. Still, it gave me a smile. I may continue the series, but not right away.	71:https://www.goodreads.com/book/show/631233
