5:000067280	6:gr-67280	3:Typography: A Manual of Design (English and German Edition)	4:book review	60:Typography: A Manual of Design (English and German Edition)	61:Emil Ruder	62:1981	64:Hastings House Pub	68:read	69:2005-01-01	63:9780803872233	67:4/5	71:https://www.goodreads.com/book/show/67280
5:000673252	6:gr-673252	3:Anne McCaffrey's Dragonflight #1	4:book review	60:Anne McCaffrey's Dragonflight #1	61:Brynne Stephens	62:1993	64:Eclipse Books	68:read	69:2020-01-01	63:9781560601760	67:3/5	71:https://www.goodreads.com/book/show/673252
5:000674976	6:gr-674976	3:Sunglasses after Dark (Sonja Blue, #1)	4:book review	60:Sunglasses after Dark (Sonja Blue, #1)	61:Nancy A. Collins	62:1989	64:Onyx/New American Library	68:read	69:1994-01-01	63:9780451401472	67:5/5	71:https://www.goodreads.com/book/show/674976
5:000678049	6:gr-678049	3:Ethics: A Very Short Introduction	4:book review	60:Ethics: A Very Short Introduction	61:Simon Blackburn	62:2009	64:Oxford University Press	68:read	69:2022-04-16	63:9780192804426	67:2/5	70:Short introduction indeed. There was some questionable structure to this work, and it reads a bit more like a rambling blog post than any sort of philosophical work. Even so, it's accessible and introduces some of the basic ideas and schools of thought in the subject.	71:https://www.goodreads.com/book/show/678049
5:000678071	6:gr-678071	3:Doctor Who: Wooden Heart	4:book review	60:Doctor Who: Wooden Heart	61:Martin Day	62:2007	64:Random House UK	68:read	69:2013-08-15	63:9781846072260	67:3/5	71:https://www.goodreads.com/book/show/678071
5:000678072	6:gr-678072	3:Doctor Who: The Art of Destruction	4:book review	60:Doctor Who: The Art of Destruction	61:Stephen Cole	62:2007	64:Random House UK	68:read	69:2013-03-17	63:9780563486510	67:1/5	70:This is the first Doctor Who book I couldn't even finish. It was pretty awful. I couldn't tell who was who at all. None of the characters were distinct, even the Doctor. It didn't sound like the 10th Doctor in the least, and many times I found myself reading his dialogue thinking he was one of the African scientists only to learn my mistake after he finished speaking. Totally confusing, not engaging.	71:https://www.goodreads.com/book/show/678072
