5:000068783	6:gr-68783	3:Girl, Interrupted	4:book review	60:Girl, Interrupted	61:Susanna Kaysen	62:1994	64:Vintage	68:read	69:1997-01-01	63:9780679746041	67:3/5	71:https://www.goodreads.com/book/show/68783
5:006890220	6:gr-6890220	3:Mind Games (The Disillusionists, #1)	4:book review	60:Mind Games (The Disillusionists, #1)	61:Carolyn Crane	62:2010	64:Spectra	68:read	69:2011-05-28	63:9780553592610	67:4/5	70:What a fun read! Wonderful characters and a really neat "magic" system. There's quite a bit of romance-novel aspects in here, but they don't overwhelm the story. It's a really quick read and worth the time.	71:https://www.goodreads.com/book/show/6890220
5:000068930	6:gr-68930	3:They Do It With Mirrors (Miss Marple, #6)	4:book review	60:They Do It With Mirrors (Miss Marple, #6)	61:Agatha Christie	62:2000	64:Signet	68:read	69:2013-06-02	63:9780451199904	67:4/5	71:https://www.goodreads.com/book/show/68930
5:000689335	6:gr-689335	3:Book of Poisons: A Guide for Writers	4:book review	60:Book of Poisons: A Guide for Writers	61:Serita Stevens	62:2007	64:Writer's Digest Books	68:read	69:2013-01-21	63:9781582974569	67:5/5	70:If you are going to write about poisons or run an RPG with poisons taking a major role, this book is invaluable. Get it now, read it cover to cover, then keep it in your pile when you run or write anything.	71:https://www.goodreads.com/book/show/689335
5:006905041	6:gr-6905041	3:Land of Lisp: Learn to Program in Lisp, One Game at a Time!	4:book review	60:Land of Lisp: Learn to Program in Lisp, One Game at a Time!	61:Conrad Barski	62:2010	64:No Starch Press	68:read	63:9781593272005	67:5/5	71:https://www.goodreads.com/book/show/6905041
5:000694962	6:gr-694962	3:Paradoxes	4:book review	60:Paradoxes	61:R.M. Sainsbury	62:1995	64:Cambridge University Press	68:read	69:2003-01-01	63:9780521483476	67:4/5	70:I read this back in high school and it it was a great introduction to Zeno's paradox, vagueness heap, and more. It offers enough depth as a thorough introduction, and prepares the mind well to touch on these topics in more advanced philosophies.	71:https://www.goodreads.com/book/show/694962
5:006963764	6:gr-6963764	3:Captain's Share (Golden Age of the Solar Clipper, #5)	4:book review	60:Captain's Share (Golden Age of the Solar Clipper, #5)	61:Nathan Lowell	62:2013	68:read	69:2014-09-21	63:9781937475673	67:4/5	70:The series is back on track with this book. Once again we can follow the steadfast Ishmael Horatio Wang in his almost-adventures across the Deep Dark. Will he face danger? Not quite. Will he struggle against enemies? Not really. Will he risk life and limb for amazing profits? Um, probably not. That's not very prudent.\n\nSomehow this series still excites me despite having none of the characteristics of enjoyable genre fiction. I can't explain it and that's okay.	71:https://www.goodreads.com/book/show/6963764
