5:000773230	6:gr-773230	3:Teach Yourself Visually Handspinning (Teach Yourself Visually Consumer)	4:book review	60:Teach Yourself Visually Handspinning (Teach Yourself Visually Consumer)	61:Judith MacKenzie McCuin	62:2007	64:Visual	68:read	69:2020-02-17	63:9780470098455	67:4/5	70:This was a fantastic help in my spinning. I've learned so much from watching Youtube videos, but I kept running into trouble in different places. What can I say, youtubers aren't always great teachers. This book covers WHY you might spin using different draw techniques for different materials. It has troubleshooting guides, and lots of guidance on overspinning and underspinning. It covers a variety of ways to do each step, comparing spindle & wheel techniques. It is a very good book.	71:https://www.goodreads.com/book/show/773230
5:000007733	6:gr-7733	3:Gulliver's Travels	4:book review	60:Gulliver's Travels	61:Jonathan Swift	62:2017	64:Penguin	68:read	69:1997-01-01	63:9780141439495	67:2/5	71:https://www.goodreads.com/book/show/7733
5:000077377	6:gr-77377	3:How to Shit in the Woods: An Environmentally Sound Approach to a Lost Art	4:book review	60:How to Shit in the Woods: An Environmentally Sound Approach to a Lost Art	61:Kathleen Meyer	62:1994	64:Ten Speed Press	68:read	69:2004-01-01	63:9780898156270	67:3/5	71:https://www.goodreads.com/book/show/77377
5:007743175	6:gr-7743175	3:A Memory of Light (The Wheel of Time, #14)	4:book review	60:A Memory of Light (The Wheel of Time, #14)	61:Robert Jordan	62:2013	64:Tor Books	68:read	69:2013-04-21	63:9780765325952	67:5/5	70:Well, I can't believe the series is finally done. It seems like most of my reading life has been surrounding these books. \n\nWhat to say about the book itself? Well, it's about 90% battle and I for one think that makes perfect sense. This is not a stand alone book, it is a culmination of 13 others. Plus, Brandon Sanderson may be one of the best battle writers out there today. He deftly wove stories through a war on a massive scale without it ever resorting to confusion. \n\nI could cover characterization and pacing but really all you need to know is that the ending is worth it. If you've managed to read 13 books in the series you are probably going to finish. Now you can do so with some confidence.	71:https://www.goodreads.com/book/show/7743175
5:007747374	6:gr-7747374	3:I Am Number Four (Lorien Legacies, #1)	4:book review	60:I Am Number Four (Lorien Legacies, #1)	61:Pittacus Lore	62:2010	64:HarperCollins	68:read	69:2013-10-04	63:9780061969553	67:4/5	71:https://www.goodreads.com/book/show/7747374
5:000775021	6:gr-775021	3:Hiking in Alaska (Lonely Planet Hiking)	4:book review	60:Hiking in Alaska (Lonely Planet Hiking)	61:Jim Dufresne	62:2000	64:Lonely Planet Publications	68:read	69:2006-01-01	63:9781864500387	67:3/5	71:https://www.goodreads.com/book/show/775021
5:000077507	6:gr-77507	3:Red Mars (Mars Trilogy, #1)	4:book review	60:Red Mars (Mars Trilogy, #1)	61:Kim Stanley Robinson	62:1993	64:Spectra Books	68:read	69:2021-12-17	63:9780553560732	67:2/5	70:Overall I found this book pretty boring. I didn't connect much with the characters and their mission and its particulars didn't drag me along without them. The few characters who felt well-reasoned and rounded at the start just sort of felt abandoned into characatures later on. The descriptive sprawl of endless nothingness of Mars is a pretty apt analogy to what it felt like reading this.\n\nI should note that the novel is well researched and thought out. The political questions it raises about the reality of a martian settlement are sound. Sound, but boring.	71:https://www.goodreads.com/book/show/77507
5:000077566	6:gr-77566	3:Hyperion (Hyperion Cantos, #1)	4:book review	60:Hyperion (Hyperion Cantos, #1)	61:Dan Simmons	62:1990	64:Bantam Doubleday Dell Publishing Group	68:read	69:2018-02-25	63:9780553283686	67:3/5	70:It caught my interest early and carried it well for much of the book. I lost interest during the Consul's story, and gave up completely in the last 100 pages.	71:https://www.goodreads.com/book/show/77566
