5:078790069	6:gr-78790069	3:Immortal Moments (Beneath the Dragoneye Moons, #6)	4:book review	60:Immortal Moments (Beneath the Dragoneye Moons, #6)	61:Selkie Myth	62:2022	68:read	69:2023-03-25	67:5/5	71:https://www.goodreads.com/book/show/78790069
5:078790668	6:gr-78790668	3:Return to Remus (Beneath the Dragoneye Moons, #7)	4:book review	60:Return to Remus (Beneath the Dragoneye Moons, #7)	61:Selkie Myth	62:2022	68:read	69:2023-03-25	67:4/5	71:https://www.goodreads.com/book/show/78790668
5:007896271	6:gr-7896271	3:Hypothermia (Inspector Erlendur #8)	4:book review	60:Hypothermia (Inspector Erlendur #8)	61:Arnaldur Indriðason	62:2010	64:Minotaur Books	68:read	69:2017-04-19	63:9780312569914	67:2/5	70:I was really into this story at the beginning. I'm absolutely obsessed with Iceland and the setting drew me in quickly. I could place myself at each location and I loved meeting the cast of characters. That is, for the first third of the book.\n\nAfter that things began to turn. The book fell into a repetitive pattern with the interview style dialog. Not much was revealed naturally. So much was force-fed and the revelations became tedious and drawn out. The revolving door of characters became more two dimensional and before I knew it I had lost all drive to know the conclusion.	71:https://www.goodreads.com/book/show/7896271
5:000793834	6:gr-793834	3:The Empire Strikes Back: The National Public Radio Dramatization	4:book review	60:The Empire Strikes Back: The National Public Radio Dramatization	61:Brian Daley	62:1995	64:Del Rey	68:read	69:2023-12-03	63:9780345396051	67:1/5	70:This was pretty bad. Empire is arguably the strongest of the Star Wars films (though I may prefer Rogue One myself), but this extended script version in the radio drama did it dirty. The extensions on scenes and dialogue undercut what was working, weakening the overall story. Han was outright creepy instead of roguish, and Vader continues to feel like a cartoon villain. He just never stops talking!\n\nIf you were curious about checking out this format for the Star Wars stories, you can probably just skip it. You're not missing anything.	71:https://www.goodreads.com/book/show/793834
