5:000099702	6:gr-99702	3:Island in the Sea of Time (Nantucket, #1)	4:book review	60:Island in the Sea of Time (Nantucket, #1)	61:S.M. Stirling	62:1998	64:Ace	68:read	69:2018-07-15	63:9780451456755	67:3/5	70:This is the start of an excellent series. There's so much detail and thought given in, such rich history brought to life, and vivid characters.	71:https://www.goodreads.com/book/show/99702
5:009993738	6:gr-9993738	3:Zen and the Art of Raising Chickens: Way of the Hen	4:book review	60:Zen and the Art of Raising Chickens: Way of the Hen	61:Clea Danaan	62:2010	68:read	69:2015-03-09	67:2/5	70:There wasn't much to mark this book as special, really. It had some interesting thoughts on our relationship with nature and homesteading, but the organization of the book felt as meandering as a chicken scratching at the ground. Toward the latter half of the book the author started losing her focus from the Way of the Hen into a general disorder of new age themed sentiments that didn't mesh with the message and detracted from her ability to connect on a wide scale.\n\nOne nice note is that for some reason my two year old son loved when I would read this to him. He didn't understand the words much, but he was always asking for the "bawk-bawk book". For that reason alone this will bring a smile to my face whenever I think of it.	71:https://www.goodreads.com/book/show/9993738
